obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (71941)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71941&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) This Act may be called the Central Excise Act,`
  line 1944.]
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2[* * *].`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^3`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by ibid, s. 71, for sub-section (1), (w.e.f. 28-9-1996).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 41 of 1954, s. 2 and Sch, (w.e.f. 8-10-1954).`
  line
  line `3. 28th February, 1944, see Notification No. III-D, dated 26th February, 1944, Gazette of India, Extra., 1994, p. 293.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (71942)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71942&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "adjudicating authority" means any authority competent to pass any order or decision under`
  line `this Act, but does not include the Central Board of Excise and Customs constituted under the Central`
  line `Boards of Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963) ^2[Commissioner of Central Excise (Appeals) or Appellate`
  line Tribunal;]
  line
  line `(aa) "Appellate Tribunal" means the Customs, Excise and ^3[Service Tax] Appellate Tribunal`
  line `constituted under Section 129 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962);]`
  line
  line `^4[(aaa)] "broker" or "commission agent" means a person who in the ordinary course of business`
  line `makes contracts for the sale or purchase of excisable goods for others;`
  line
  line `^5[(b) "Central Excise Officer" means the ^6[Principal Chief Commissioner of Central Excise, Chief`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise, Principal Commissioner of Central Excise], Commissioner of Central`
  line `Excise (Appeals), Additional Commissioner of Central Excise, ^7[Joint Commissioner of Central`
  line `Excise,] ^8[Assistant Commissioner of Central Excise or Deputy Commissioner of Central Excise] or`
  line `any other officer of the Central Excise Department, or any person (including an officer of the State`
  line `Government) invested by the Central Board of Excise and Customs constituted under the Central`
  line `Boards of Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963) with any of the powers of a Central Excise Officer under`
  line `this Act;]`
  line
  line `(c) "curing" includes wilting, drying, fermenting and any process for rendering an unmanufactured`
  line `product fit for marketing or manufacture;`
  line
  line `(d) "excisable goods" means goods specified in ^9[the Fourth Schedule] as being subject to a duty`
  line `of excise^10`
  line `and includes salt;`
  line
  line `^11[Explanation.-- For the purposes of this clause, "goods" includes any article, material or substance`
  line `which is capable of being bought and sold for a consideration and such goods shall be deemed to be`
  line marketable.]
  line
  line `(e) "factory" means any premises, including the precincts thereof, wherein or in any part of which`
  line `excisable goods ^12[* * *] are manufactured, or wherein or in any part of which any manufacturing`
  line `process connected with the production of these goods is being carried on or is ordinarily carried on;`
  line
  line `^13[(ee) "Fund" means the Consumer Welfare Fund established under Section 12C;]`
  line
  line `^14[(f) "manufacture" includes any process--`
  line
  line `(i) incidental or ancillary to the completion of a manufactured product;`
  line
  line `(ii) which is specified in relation to any goods in the Section or Chapter Notes of ^15[the Fourth`
  line `Schedule] as amounting to ^16[manufacture ;or],`
  line
  line `^17[(iii) which, in relation to the goods specified in the Third Schedule, involves packing or`
  line `repacking of such goods in a unit container or labelling or re-labelling of containers including the`
  line `declaration or alteration of retail sale price on it or adoption of any other treatment on the goods to`
  line `render the product marketable to the consumer;]`
  line
  line `and the word "manufacture" shall be construed accordingly and shall include not only a person`
  line `who employs hired labour in the production or manufacture of excisable goods, but also any person`
  line `who engages in their production or manufacture on his own account;]`
  line
  line `^18[(ff) "National Tax Tribunal" means the National Tax Tribunal established under Section 3 of the`
  line `National Tax Tribunal Act, 2005 (49 of 2005);]`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "sale" and "purchase", with their grammatical variations and cognate expressions, mean any`
  line `transfer of the possession of goods by one person to another in the ordinary course of trade or business`
  line `for cash or deferred payment or other valuable consideration;`
  line
  line `(i)`
  line `^19[* * *]`
  line
  line `(j)`
  line `^20[* * *]`
  line
  line `(jj)`
  line `^21[* * *]`
  line
  line `(k) "wholesale dealer" means a person who buys or sells excisable goods wholesale for the purpose`
  line `of trade or manufacture, and includes a broker or commission agent, who, in addition to making`
  line `contracts for the sale or purchase of excisable goods for others, stocks such goods belonging to others`
  line `as an agent for the purpose of sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Sch. V, Part II-1 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 70, for "Collector of Central Excise (Appeals)".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 135, for "Gold (control)" (w.e.f. 14-05-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Clause (a) re-lettered by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Sch. V, Part II (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 71, for "clause b" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 96, for "Chief Commissioner of Central Excise" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 120(i) (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by ibid, s. 119, for Assistant Commissioner of Central Excise.`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 18 of 2017, s. 5(a), for "the First Schedule and the Second Schedule to the Central Excise Tariff Act, 1985 (5 of`
  line `1986)".`
  line
  line `10. References to the expressions "duty", "duties," "duty of excise" and "duties of excise" shall, save as otherwise expressly provided`
  line `in this Act and unless the context otherwise requires, be construed to include a reference to the special duty of excise specified`
  line `in the Second Schedule to the Central Excise Tariff Act, 1985.`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 78, (w.e.f. 10-5-2008).`
  line
  line `12. The word "other than salt" omitted by Act 18 of 2017, s. 5(b).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 2 (w.e.f. 20-2-1991). Earlier cl. (ee), ins. by Act 25 of 1950, s. 11 and Sch. IV, omitted by Act 41 of`
  line `1954, s. 2 and Sch (w.e.f. 8-10-1954).`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by Act 5 of 1986, s. 4, for Sub-clause (f) (w.e.f. 28-2-1986).`
  line
  line `15. Subs. by Act 18 of 2017, s. 5(c), for "the First Schedule to the Central Excise Tariff Act, 1985 (5 of 1986)".`
  line
  line `16. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 132(i), for "manufacture" (w.e.f. 11-5-2002).`
  line
  line `17. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 135, for sub-clause (iii). (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `18. Ins. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and Sch. (Pt. VII-1) (w.e.f. 28-12-2005).`
  line
  line `19. Clause (i) omitted by Act 33 of 1996, s. 72, (w.e.f. 28-9-1996).`
  line
  line `20. Clause (j) omitted by ibid, s. 72, (w.e.f. 28-9-1996).`
  line
  line `21. Clause (jj), omitted by Act 25 of 1950, s. 11 and Sch. IV. Earlier clause (jj) was inserted by the A.O. 1950.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (71943)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 3
  title `References of certain expressions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 91 (w.e.f. 12-5-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71943&sectionno=2A&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[2A. References of certain expressions.-- In this Act, save as otherwise expressly provided and`
  line `unless the context otherwise requires, references to the expressions "duty", "duties", "duty of excise" and`
  line `"duties of excise" shall be construed to include a reference to "Central Value Added Tax (CENVAT)".]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (71944)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Duty specified in the Fourth Schedule to be levied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2017, s. 6, for section 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71944&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1]3. Duty specified in the Fourth Schedule to be levied.-- (1) There shall be levied and collected in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed a duty of excise to be called the Central Value Added Tax (CENVAT)`
  line `on all excisable goods (excluding goods produced or manufactured in special economic zones) which are`
  line `produced or manufactured in India as, and at the rates, set forth in the Fourth Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that the duty of excise which shall be levied and collected on any excisable goods which`
  line `are produced or manufactured by a hundred per cent export oriented undertaking and brought to any`
  line `other place in India, shall be an amount equal to the aggregate of the duties of customs which would be`
  line `leviable under the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) or any other law for the time being in force, on like`
  line `goods produced or manufactured outside India if imported into India, and where the said duties of`
  line `customs are chargeable by reference to their value, the value of such excisable goods shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, be determined in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of the Customs Act, 1962 and the Customs Tariff Act, 1975 (51 of 1975).`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.-- Where in respect of any such like goods, any duty of customs leviable for the time`
  line `being in force is leviable at different rates, then, such duty shall, for the purposes of this proviso, be deemed`
  line `to be leviable at the highest of those rates.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.-- For the purposes of this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(i) "hundred per cent export-oriented undertaking” means an undertaking which has been approved`
  line `as a hundred per cent export-oriented undertaking by the board appointed in this behalf by the Central`
  line `Government in exercise of the powers conferred by Section 14 of the Industries (Development and`
  line `Regulation) Act, 1951 (65 of 1951), and the rules made under that Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) "Special Economic Zone" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (za) of Section 2 of`
  line `the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005).`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall apply in respect of all excisable goods which are produced`
  line `or manufactured in India by or on behalf of the Government, as they apply in respect of goods which are`
  line `not produced or manufactured by the Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, fix, for the purposes of levying`
  line `the said duty, tariff values of any articles enumerated, either specifically or under general headings, in the`
  line `Fourth Schedule as chargeable with duty ad valorem and may alter any tariff values for the time being in`
  line force.
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may fix different tariff values--`
  line
  line `(a) for different classes or descriptions of the same excisable goods; or`
  line
  line `(b) for excisable goods of the same class or description--`
  line
  line `(i) produced or manufactured by different classes of producers or manufacturers; or`
  line
  line `(ii) sold to different classes of buyers:`
  line
  line `Provided that in fixing different tariff values in respect of excisable goods falling under`
  line `sub-clause (i) or sub-clause (ii), regard shall be had to the sale prices charged by the different classes`
  line `of producers or manufacturers or, as the case may be, the normal practice of the wholesale trade in such`
  line goods.[
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (72869)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 5
  title `Power of Central Government to charge excise duty on the basis of capacity of production in respect of notified goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72869&sectionno=3A&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[3A. Power of Central Government to charge excise duty on the basis of capacity of production`
  line `in respect of notified goods.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in Section 3, where the Central`
  line `Government, having regard to the nature of the process of manufacture or production of excisable goods of`
  line `any specified description, the extent of evasion of duty in regard to such goods or such other factors as may`
  line `be relevant, is of the opinion that it is necessary to safeguard the interest of revenue, specify, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, such goods as notified goods and there shall be levied and collected duty of excise`
  line `on such goods in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a notification is issued under sub-section (1), the Central Government may, by rules,--`
  line
  line `(a) provide the manner for determination of the annual capacity of production of the factory, in`
  line `which such goods are produced, by an officer not below the rank of Assistant ^2[Principal Commissioner`
  line `of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise and such annual capacity shall be deemed to be`
  line `the annual production of such goods by such factory; or`
  line
  line `(b)(i) specify the factor relevant to the production of such goods and the quantity that is deemed to`
  line `be produced by use of a unit of such factor; and`
  line
  line `(ii) provide for the determination of the annual capacity of production of the factory in which such`
  line `goods are produced on the basis of such factor by an officer not below the rank of Assistant ^2[Principal`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] and such annual capacity of`
  line `production shall be deemed to be the annual production of such goods by such factory:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a factory producing notified goods is in operation during a part of the year`
  line `only, the annual production thereof shall be calculated on proportionate basis of the annual capacity of`
  line `production:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in a case where the factor relevant to the production is altered or modified at`
  line `any time during the year, the annual production shall be re-determined on a proportionate basis having`
  line `regard to such alteration or modification.`
  line
  line `(3) The duty of excise on notified goods shall be levied, at such rate, on the unit of production or, as`
  line `the case may be, on such factor relevant to the production, as the Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, specify, and collected in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line `Provided that where a factory producing notified goods did not produce the notified goods during any`
  line `continuous period of fifteen days or more, the duty calculated on a proportionate basis shall be abated in`
  line `respect of such period if the manufacturer of such goods fulfils such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this section shall not apply to goods produced or manufactured, by a hundred per`
  line `cent export-oriented undertaking and brought to any other place in India.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.-- For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that for the purposes of Section 3 of`
  line `the Customs Tariff Act, 1975 (51 of 1975), the duty of excise leviable on the notified goods shall be deemed`
  line `to be the duty of excise leviable on such goods under the ^3[Fourth Schedule, read with any notification for`
  line `the time being in force.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.-- For the purposes of this section, the expression hundred per cent export-oriented`
  line `undertaking" shall have the meaning assigned to it in Section 3.`
  line
  line `^4[Explanation 3.-- For the purposes of sub-sections (2) and (3), the word "factor" includes "factors".]]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 79. (w.e.f. 10-5-2008) Prior s. 3A was omitted by Act 14 of 2001, s. 121.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 2017, s. 7, for "First Schedule and the Second Schedule to the Central Excise Tariff Act, 1985 (5 of 1986)".`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 92.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_b:
  sectionId (71946)
  sectionNo 3B
  orderNo 6
  title `Emergency power of Central Government to increase duty of excise.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2017, s. 8.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71946&sectionno=3B&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_3_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[3B. Emergency power of Central Government to increase duty of excise.-- (1) Where, in respect`
  line `of any goods, the Central Government is satisfied that the duty leviable thereon under Section 3 should be`
  line `increased and that circumstances exist which render it necessary to take immediate action, the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend the Fourth Schedule to substitute the rate`
  line `of duty specified therein in respect of such goods in the following manner, namely--`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where the rate of duty as specified in the Fourth Schedule as in force immediately`
  line `before the issue of such notification is nil, a rate of duty not exceeding fifty per cent ad valorem`
  line `expressed in any form or method;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, a rate of duty which shall not be more than twice the rate of duty specified in`
  line `respect of such goods in the Fourth Schedule as in force immediately before the issue of the said`
  line `notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall not issue any notification under this sub-section`
  line `for substituting the rate of duty in respect of any goods as specified by an earlier notification issued under this sub-section by that Government before such earlier notification has been approved with`
  line `or without modifications under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, the term "form or method", in relation to a rate of`
  line `duty of excise, means the basis, including valuation, weight, number, length, area, volume or any other`
  line `measure, on which the duty may be levied.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under sub-section (1) shall be laid before each House of Parliament, if it is in`
  line `session, as soon as may be after the issue of the notification, and, if it is not in session, within seven days`
  line `of its reassembly, and the Central Government shall seek the approval of Parliament to the notification by`
  line `a resolution moved within a period of fifteen days beginning with the day on which the notification is so`
  line `laid before the House of the People and if Parliament makes any modification in the notification or directs`
  line `that the notification should cease to have effect, the notification shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, but without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) Any notification issued under sub-section (1), including a notification approved or modified under`
  line `sub-section (2), may be rescinded by the Central Government at any time by issuing notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_c:
  sectionId (71947)
  sectionNo 3C
  orderNo 7
  title `Power of Central Government to amend Fourth Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2017, s. 8.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71947&sectionno=3C&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_3_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[3C. Power of Central Government to amend Fourth Schedule.--(1) Where the Central`
  line `Government is satisfied that it is necessary so to do in the public interest, it may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, amend the Fourth Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that such amendment shall not alter or affect in any manner the rates specified in the`
  line `Fourth Schedule at which the duties of excise shall be leviable on the goods specified therein.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (71948)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 8
  title `Valuation of excisable goods for purposes of charging of duty of excise.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71948&sectionno=4&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Valuation of excisable goods for purposes of charging of duty of excise.--- (1) Where under this`
  line `Act, the duty of excise is chargeable on any excisable goods with reference to their value, then, on each`
  line `removal of the goods, such value shall--`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where the goods are sold by the assessee, for delivery at the time and place of the`
  line `removal, the assessee and the buyer of the goods are not related and the price is the sole consideration`
  line `for the sale, be the transaction value;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, including the case where the goods are not sold, be the value determined in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.-- For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the price-cum-duty of the`
  line `excisable goods sold by the assessee shall be the price actually paid to him for the goods sold and the money`
  line `value of the additional consideration, if any, flowing directly or indirectly from the buyer to the assessee in`
  line `connection with the sale of such goods, and such price-cum-duty, excluding sales tax and other taxes, if`
  line `any, actually paid, shall be deemed to include the duty payable on such goods.]`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this section shall not apply in respect of any excisable goods for which a tariff`
  line `value has been fixed under sub-section (2) of Section 3.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "assessee" means the person who is liable to pay the duty of excise under this Act and includes`
  line `his agent;`
  line
  line `(b) persons shall be deemed to be "related" if--`
  line
  line `(i) they are inter-connected undertakings;`
  line
  line `(ii) they are relatives;`
  line
  line `(iii) amongst them the buyer is a relative and a distributor of the assessee, or a sub-distributor`
  line `of such distributor; or`
  line
  line `(iv) they are so associated that they have interest, directly or indirectly, in the business of each`
  line other.
  line
  line `Explanation.In this clause--`
  line
  line `^3[(i) "inter-connected undertakings" means two or more undertakings which are inter-connected`
  line `with each other in any of the following manners, namely---`
  line
  line `(A) if one owns or controls the other;`
  line
  line `(B) where the undertakings are owned by firms, if such firms have one or more common partners;`
  line
  line `(C) where the undertakings are owned by bodies corporate,--`
  line
  line `(I) if one body corporate manages the other body corporate; or`
  line
  line `(II) if one body corporate is a subsidiary of the other body corporate; or`
  line
  line `(III) if the bodies corporate are under the same management; or`
  line
  line `(IV) if one body corporate exercises control over the other body corporate in any other`
  line manner;
  line
  line `(D) where one undertaking is owned by a body corporate and the other is owned by a firm, if one`
  line `or more partners of the firm,--`
  line
  line `(I) hold, directly or indirectly, not less than fifty per cent of the shares, whether preference or`
  line `equity, of the body corporate; or`
  line
  line `(II) exercise control, directly or indirectly, whether as director or otherwise, over the body`
  line corporate;
  line
  line `(E) if one is owned by a body corporate and the other is owned by a firm having bodies corporate`
  line `as its partners, if such bodies corporate are under the same management;`
  line
  line `(F) if the undertakings are owned or controlled by the same person or by the same group;`
  line
  line `(G) if one is connected with the other either directly or through any number of undertakings which`
  line `are inter-connected undertakings within the meaning of one or more of the foregoing sub-clauses.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.-- For the purposes of this clause, two bodies corporate shall be deemed to be under`
  line `the same management--`
  line
  line `(i) if one such body corporate exercises control over the other or both are under the control of the`
  line `same group or any of the constituents of the same group; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if the Managing Director or manager of one such body corporate is the Managing Director or`
  line `manager of the other; or`
  line
  line `(iii) if one such body corporate holds not less than one-fourth of the equity shares in the other or`
  line `controls the composition of not less than one-fourth of the total membership of the Board of Directors`
  line `of the other; or`
  line
  line `(iv) if one or more directors of one such body corporate constitute, or at any time within a period`
  line `of six months immediately preceding the day when the question arises as to whether such bodies`
  line `corporate are under the same management, constituted (whether independently or together with`
  line `relatives of such directors or employees of the first mentioned body corporate) one-fourth of the`
  line `directors of the other; or`
  line
  line `(v) if the same individual or individuals belonging to a group, while holding (whether by themselves`
  line `or together with their relatives) not less than one-fourth of the equity shares in one such body corporate`
  line `also hold (whether by themselves or together with their relatives) not less than one-fourth of the equity`
  line `shares in the other; or`
  line
  line `(vi) if the same body corporate or bodies corporate belonging to a group, holding, whether`
  line `independently or along with its or their subsidiary or subsidiaries, not less than one-fourth of the equity`
  line `shares in one body corporate, also hold not less than one-fourth of the equity shares in the other; or`
  line
  line `(vii) if not less than one-fourth of the total voting power in relation to each of the two bodies`
  line `corporate is exercised or controlled by the same individual (whether independently or together with his`
  line `relatives) or the same body corporate (whether independently or together with its subsidiaries); or`
  line
  line `(viii) if not less than one-fourth of the total voting power in relation to each of the two bodies`
  line `corporate is exercised or controlled by the same individuals belonging to a group or by the same bodies`
  line `corporate belonging to a group, or jointly by such individual or individuals and one or more of such`
  line `bodies corporate; or`
  line
  line `(ix) if the directors of one such body corporate are accustomed to act in accordance with the`
  line `directions or instructions of one or more of the directors of the other, or if the directors of both the`
  line `bodies corporate are accustomed to act in accordance with the directions or instructions of an individual,`
  line `whether belonging to a group or not.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.-- If a group exercises control over a body corporate, that body corporate and every`
  line `other body corporate, which is a constituent of, or controlled by, the group shall be deemed to be under`
  line `the same management.`
  line
  line `Explanation III.-- If two or more bodies corporate under the same management hold, in the`
  line `aggregate, not less than one-fourth equity share capital in any other body corporate, such other body`
  line `corporate shall be deemed to be under the same management as the first mentioned bodies corporate.`
  line
  line `Explanation IV.-- In determining whether or not two or more bodies corporate are under the same`
  line `management, the shares held by financial institutions in such bodies corporate shall not be taken into`
  line account.
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `Undertaking B is inter-connected with undertaking A and undertaking C is inter-connected with`
  line `undertaking B. Undertaking C is inter-connected with undertaking A; if undertaking D is inter-connected`
  line `with undertaking C, undertaking D will be inter-connected with undertaking B and consequently with`
  line `undertaking A; and so on.`
  line
  line `Explanation V --- For the purposes of this clause, "group" means a group of--`
  line
  line `(i) two or more individuals, associations of individuals, firms, trusts, trustees or bodies corporate`
  line `(excluding financial institutions), or any combination thereof, which exercises, or is established to be`
  line `in a position to exercise, control, directly or indirectly, over any body corporate, firm or trust; or`
  line
  line `(ii) "associated persons".`
  line
  line `Explanation VI.--- For the purposes of this clause,--`
  line
  line `(I) a group of persons who are able, directly or indirectly, to control the policy of a body corporate,`
  line `firm or trust, without having a controlling interest in that body corporate, firm or trust, shall also be`
  line `deemed to be in a position to exercise control over it;`
  line
  line `(II) associated persons--`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to a director of a body corporate, means--`
  line
  line `(i) a relative of such director, and includes a firm in which such director or his relative is a`
  line partner;
  line
  line `(ii) any trust of which any such director or his relative is a trustee;`
  line
  line `(iii) any company of which such director, whether independently or together with his`
  line `relatives, constitutes one-fourth of its Board of Directors;`
  line
  line `(iv) any other body corporate, at any general meeting of which not less than one-fourth of`
  line `the total number of directors of such other body corporate are appointed or controlled by the`
  line `director of the first mentioned body corporate or his relative, whether acting singly or jointly;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to the partner of a firm, means a relative of such partner and includes`
  line `any other partner of such firm; and`
  line
  line `(c) in relation to the trustee of a trust, means any other trustee of such trust;`
  line
  line `(III) where any person is an associated person in relation to another, the letter shall also be`
  line `deemed to be an associated person in relation to the former;]`
  line
  line `(b) "relative" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (41) of Section 2 of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(c) "place of removal" means--`
  line
  line `(i) a factory or any other place or premises of production or manufacture of the`
  line `excisable goods;`
  line
  line `(ii) a warehouse or any other place or premises wherein the excisable goods have been`
  line `permitted to be deposited without ^4[payment of duty;]`
  line `^5[(iii) a depot, premises of a consignment agent or any other place or premises from`
  line `where the excisable goods are to be sold after their clearance from the factory,]`
  line `from where such goods are removed;`
  line
  line `^5[(cc) "time of removal", in respect of the excisable goods removed from the place of`
  line `removal referred to in sub-clause (iii) of clause (c), shall be deemed to be the time at which`
  line `such goods are cleared from the factory;]`
  line
  line `(d) "transaction value" means the price actually paid or payable for the goods, when sold,`
  line `and includes in addition to the amount charged as price, any amount that the buyer is liable to pay to, or on behalf of, the assessee, by reason of, or in connection with the sale, whether`
  line `payable at the time of the sale or at any other time, including, but not limited to, any amount`
  line `charged for, or to make provision for, advertising or publicity, marketing and selling`
  line `organization expenses, storage, outward handling, servicing, warranty, commission or any`
  line `other matter; but does not include the amount of duty of excise, sales tax and other taxes, if`
  line `any, actually paid or actually payable on such goods.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 94 (w.e.f. 1-7-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 136, (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 133, for "(i)".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 136, for "payment of duty,".`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by, ibid, s. 136.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (71949)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 9
  title `Valuation of excisable goods with reference to retail sale price.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71949&sectionno=4A&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[4A. Valuation of excisable goods with reference to retail sale price.-- (1) The Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify any goods, in relation to which it is required, under the`
  line `provisions of the ^2[Legal Metrology Act, 2009 (1 of 2010) or the rules made thereunder or under any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, to declare on the package thereof the retail sale price of such goods, to`
  line `which the provisions of sub-section (2) shall apply.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the goods specified under sub-section (1) are excisable goods and are chargeable to duty of`
  line `excise with reference to value, then, notwithstanding anything contained in Section 4, such value shall be`
  line `deemed to be the retail sale price declared on such goods less such amount of abatement, if any, from such`
  line `retail sale price as the Central Government may allow by notification in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, for the purpose of allowing any abatement under sub-section (2),`
  line `take into account the amount of duty of excise, sales tax and other taxes, if any, payable on such goods.`
  line
  line `^3[(4) Where any goods specified under sub-section (1) are excisable goods and the manufacturer--`
  line
  line `(a) removes such goods from the place of manufacture, without declaring the retail sale price of`
  line `such goods on the packages or declares a retail sale price which is not the retail sale price as required`
  line `to be declared under the provisions of the Act, rules or other law as referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1); or`
  line
  line `(b) tampers with, obliterates or alters the retail sale price declared on the package of such goods`
  line `after their removal from the place of manufacture,`
  line `then, such goods shall be liable to confiscation and the retail sale price of such goods shall be`
  line `ascertained in the prescribed manner and such price shall be deemed to be the retail sale price for the`
  line `purposes of this section.`
  line
  line `^4[Explanation 1.--For the purposes of this section, “retail sale price” means the maximum price at`
  line `which the excisable goods in packaged form may be sold to the ultimate consumer and includes all taxes`
  line `local or otherwise, freight, transport charges, commission payable to dealers, and all charges towards advertisement, delivery, packing, forwarding and the like, as the case may be, and the price is the sole`
  line `consideration for such sale:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case the provisions of the Act, rules or other law as referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `require to declare on the package, the retail sale price excluding any taxes, local or otherwise, the retail`
  line `sale price shall be construed accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.-- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) where on the package of any excisable goods more than one retail sale price is declared, the`
  line `maximum of such retail sale price shall be deemed to be the retail sale price;`
  line
  line `(b) where the retail sale price, declared on packages of any excisable goods at the time of its`
  line `clearance from the place of manufacture, is altered to increase the retail sale price, such altered retail`
  line `sale price shall be deemed to be the retail sale price;`
  line
  line `(c) where different retail sale prices are declared on different packages for the sale of any excisable`
  line `goods in packaged form in different areas, each such retail sale price shall be the retail sale price for`
  line `the purposes of valuation of the excisable goods intended to be sold in the area to which the retail sale`
  line `price relates.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 82.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-8-2011).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 137, for sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 105.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (71950)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 10
  title `Remission of duty on goods found deficient in quantity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 1978, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-7-1978). The original section was omitted by Act 41 of 1954, s. 2 and Sch.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71950&sectionno=5&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[5. Remission of duty on goods found deficient in quantity.-- (1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `rules made under this section, provide for remission of duty of excise leviable on any excisable goods which`
  line `due to any natural cause are found to be deficient in quantity.`
  line
  line `(2) Any rules made under sub-section (1) may, having regard to the nature of the excisable goods or of`
  line `processing or of curing thereof, the period of their storage or transit and other relevant considerations, fix`
  line `the limit or limits of percentage beyond which no such remission shall be allowed:`
  line
  line `Provided that different limit or limits of percentage may be fixed for different varieties of the same`
  line `excisable goods or for different areas or for different seasons.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (71951)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to grant exemption from duty of excise.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71951&sectionno=5A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Power to grant exemption from duty of excise.--(1) If the Central Government is satisfied that`
  line `it is necessary in the public interest so to do, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, exempt generally`
  line `either absolutely or subject to such conditions (to be fulfilled before or after removal) as may be specified`
  line `in the notification, excisable goods of any specified description from the whole or any part of the duty of`
  line `excise leviable thereon:`
  line
  line `Provided that, unless specifically provided in such notification, no exemption therein shall apply to`
  line `excisable goods which are produced or manufactured--`
  line
  line `(i) in a ^2[free trade zone`
  line `^3[* * *]] and brought to any other place in India; or`
  line
  line `(ii) by a hundred per cent export-oriented undertaking and ^4[rought to any other place in India].`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this proviso,`
  line `^2["free trade zone" ^5[* * *] and hundred per cent export-oriented`
  line `undertaking" shall have the same meanings as in Explanation 2 to sub-section (1) of Section 3.`
  line
  line `^6[(1A) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that where an exemption under sub-section (1)`
  line `in respect of any excisable goods from the whole of the duty of excise leviable thereon has been granted`
  line `absolutely, the manufacturer of such excisable goods shall not pay the duty of excise on such goods.]`
  line
  line `^7[(2) If the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary in the public interest so to do, it may, by`
  line `special order in each case, exempt from the payment of duty of excise, under circumstances of an`
  line `exceptional nature to be stated in such order, any excisable goods on which duty of excise is leviable.]`
  line
  line `^8[(2A) The Central Government may, if it considers it necessary or expedient so to do for the purpose`
  line `of clarifying the scope or applicability of any notification issued under sub-section (1) or order issued under`
  line `sub-section (2), insert an explanation in such notification or order, as the case may be, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette at any time within one year of issue of the notification under sub-section (1) or order under`
  line `sub-section (2), and every such explanation shall have effect as if it had always been the part of the first`
  line `notification or order, as the case may be.]`
  line
  line `(3) An exemption under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) in respect of any excisable goods from any`
  line `part of the duty of excise leviable thereon (the duty of excise leviable thereon being hereinafter referred to`
  line `as the statutory duty) may be granted by providing for the levy of a duty on such goods at a rate expressed`
  line `in a form or method different from the form or method in which the statutory duty is leviable and any`
  line `exemption granted in relation to any excisable goods in the manner provided in this sub-section shall have`
  line `effect subject to the condition that the duty of excise chargeable on such goods shall in no case exceed the`
  line `statutory duty.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- "Form or method", in relation to a rate of duty of excise means the basis, namely,`
  line `valuation, weight, number, length, area, volume or other measure with reference to which the duty is`
  line leviable.
  line
  line `(4) Every notification issued under sub-rule (1), and every order made under sub-rule (2), of Rule 8 of`
  line `the Central Excise Rules, 1944, and in force immediately before the commencement of the Customs and Central Excises Laws (Amendment) Act, 1988 shall be deemed to have been issued or made under the`
  line `provisions of this section and shall continue to have the same force and effect after such commencement`
  line `until it is amended, varied, rescinded or superseded under the provisions of this section.]`
  line
  line `^9[(5) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2-A) shall, unless otherwise`
  line `provided, come into force on the date of its issue by the Central Government for publication in the Official`
  line Gazette.]
  line
  line `(6)`
  line `^10[* * *ic9533]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 1988, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-7-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 122, for "free trade zone".`
  line
  line `3. The words "or a special economic zone" omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 134 (w.e.f. a date to be notified).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 122, for "allowed to be sold in India",.`
  line
  line `5. The words ", special economic zone" omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 134 (w.e.f. a date to be notified).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 75.`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 138, for "sub-section (2)".`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 134.`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, S. 142(i), for clause (5).`
  line
  line `10. Clause (6) Omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 142(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_b:
  sectionId (71952)
  sectionNo 5B
  orderNo 12
  title `Non-reversal of CENVAT credit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 116.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71952&sectionno=5B&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[5B. Non-reversal of CENVAT credit.-- Where an assessee has paid duty of excise on a final product`
  line `and has been allowed credit of the duty or tax or cess paid on inputs, capital goods and input services used`
  line `in making of the said product, but subsequently the process of making the said product is held by the court`
  line `as not chargeable to excise duty, the Central Government may, by notification, order for non-reversal of`
  line `such credit allowed to the assessee subject to such conditions as may be specified in the said notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the order for non-reversal of credit shall not apply where an assessee has preferred a`
  line `claim for refund of excise duty paid by him:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may also specify in the notification referred to above`
  line `for non-reversal of credit, if any, taken by the buyer of the said product.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (71953)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 13
  title `Registration of certain persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71953&sectionno=6&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Registration of certain persons.-- Any prescribed person who is engaged in--`
  line
  line `(a) the production or manufacture or any process of production or manufacture of any specified`
  line `goods included in the ^2[First Schedule and the Second Schedule] to the Central Excise Tariff Act, 1985`
  line `(5 of 1986), or`
  line
  line `(b) the wholesale purchase or sale (whether on his own account or as a broker or commission agent)`
  line `or the storage of any specified goods included in the ^2[First Schedule and the Second Schedule to the`
  line `Central Excise Tariff Act, 1985 (5 of 1986),`
  line
  line `shall get himself registered with the proper officer in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 113(i), for section 6, (w.e.f. 14-5-1992).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 119, for "the schedule" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
