obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (71955)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 15
  title `Restriction on possession of goods specified in the Second Schedule .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71955&sectionno=8&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `From such date as may`
  line `be specified in this behalf by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette, no person shall, except as provided by rules made under this Act, have in his possession ^1[any goods specified in the`
  line `Second Schedule] in excess of such quantity as may be prescribed for the purposes of this section as the`
  line `maximum amount of such goods or of any variety of such goods which may be possessed at any one time`
  line `by such a person.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1956, s. 9, for "any excisable goods specified in this behalf in Part B of the Second Sch." (w.e.f. 27-4-`
  line `1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (71956)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 16
  title `Offences and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71956&sectionno=9&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Whoever commits any of the following offences, namely:-- ^2[(a)`
  line `contravenes any of the provisions of Section 8 or of a rule made under clause (iii) or clause (xxvii) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of Section 37;]`
  line
  line `(b) evades the payment of any duty payable under this Act;`
  line
  line `^3[(bb) removes any excisable goods in contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or any`
  line `rules made thereunder or in any way concerns himself with such removal;`
  line
  line `(bbb) acquires possession of, or in any way concerns himself in transporting, depositing, keeping,`
  line `concealing, selling or purchasing, or in any other manner deals with any excisable goods which he`
  line `knows or has reason to believe are liable to confiscation under this Act or any rule made thereunder;]`
  line
  line `^4[(bbbb) contravenes any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder in relation to`
  line `credit of any duty allowed to be utilised towards payment of excise duty on final products;]`
  line
  line `(c) fails to supply any information which he is required by rules made under this Act to supply, or`
  line `(unless with a reasonable belief, the burden of proving which shall be upon him, that the information`
  line `supplied by him is true) supplies false information;`
  line
  line `(d) attempts to commit, or abets the commission of, any of the offences mentioned in clauses (a)`
  line `and (b) of this section;`
  line `^5[shall be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of an offence relating to any excisable goods, the duty leviable thereon under this`
  line `Act exceeds ^6[fifty lakh] of rupees, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years and`
  line `with fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be recorded in the`
  line `judgment of the Court such imprisonment shall not be for a term of less than six months;`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or with fine`
  line `or with both.]`
  line
  line `^7[(2) If any person convicted of an offence under this section is again convicted of an offence under`
  line `this section, then, he shall be punishable for the second and for every subsequent offence with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to seven years and with fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be recorded in the`
  line `judgment of the Court such imprisonment shall not be for a term of less than six months.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of sub-sections (1) and (2), the following shall not be considered as special and`
  line `adequate reasons for awarding a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than six months, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the fact that the accused has been convicted for the first time for an offence under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) the fact that in any proceeding under this Act, other than a prosecution, the accused has been`
  line `ordered to pay a penalty or the goods in relation to such proceedings have been ordered to be confiscated`
  line `or any other action has been taken against him for the same act which constitutes the offence;`
  line
  line `(iii) the fact that the accused was not the principal offender and was acting merely as a carrier of`
  line `goods or otherwise was a secondary party in the commission of the offence;`
  line
  line `(iv) the age of the accused.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 9 renumbered as sub-section (1) of that section by Act 36 of 1973, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 113, for "clause (a)" (w.e.f. 14-5-1992).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 20(i)(a) (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 107 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 20(i)(b) for certain words.`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 88, for "thirty lakh".`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 20(ii).`
