obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. Certain offences to be non-cognizable.--- ^2[(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code`
  line `of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), offences under Section 9, except the offences referred to in subsection (1A), shall be non-cognizable within the meaning of that Code.`
  line
  line `(1A) The offences relating to excisable goods where the duty leviable thereon under this Act exceeds`
  line `fifty lakh rupees and punishable under clause (b) or clause (bbbb) of sub-section (1) of Section 9, shall be`
  line `cognizable and non-bailable.]`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Any offence under this chapter may, either before or after the institution of prosecution, be`
  line `compounded by the^4[Principal Chief Commissioner of Central Excise or Chief Commissioner of Central`
  line `Excise] on payment, by the person accused of the offence to the Central Government, of ^5[such`
  line `compounding amount and in such manner of compounding] as may be prescribed:]`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) a person who has been allowed to compound once in respect of any of the offences under the`
  line `provisions of clause (a), (b), (bb), (bbb), (bbbb) or (c) of sub-section (1) of Section 9;`
  line
  line `(b) a person who has been accused of committing an offence under this Act which is also an offence`
  line `under the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985);`
  line
  line `(c) a person who has been allowed to compound once in respect of any offence under this chapter`
  line `for goods of value exceeding rupees one crore;`
  line
  line `(d) a person who has been convicted by the court under this Act on or after the 30th day of`
  line `December, 2005.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by ibid, s. 21.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 89, for (1).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 79.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Chief Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 104(i) for "such compounding amount".`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 104(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_aa:
  sectionId (71958)
  sectionNo 9AA
  orderNo 18
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_aa_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 79 of 1985, s. 2 (w.e.f. 27-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71958&sectionno=9AA&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_9_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[9AA. Offences by companies.-- (1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge`
  line `or that he had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means anybody corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.]"`
obj_root_law_sections_9_b:
  sectionId (71959)
  sectionNo 9B
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of Court to publish name, place of business, etc., of persons convicted under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 21.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71959&sectionno=9B&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[9B. Power of Court to publish name, place of business, etc., of persons convicted under the`
  line `Act.-- (1) Where any person is convicted under this Act for contravention of any of the provisions thereof,`
  line `it shall be competent for the Court convicting the person to cause the name and place of business or`
  line `residence of such person, nature of the contravention, the fact that the person has been so convicted and`
  line `such other particulars as the Court may consider to be appropriate in the circumstances of the case, to be`
  line `published at the expense of such person, in such newspapers or in such manner as the Court may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) No publication under sub-section (1) shall be made until the period for preferring an appeal against`
  line `the orders of the Court has expired without any appeal having been preferred, or such an appeal, having`
  line `been preferred, has been disposed of.`
  line
  line `(3) The expenses of any publication under sub-section (1) shall be recoverable from the convicted`
  line `person as if it were a fine imposed by the Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_c:
  sectionId (71960)
  sectionNo 9C
  orderNo 20
  title `Presumption of culpable mental state.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 21.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71960&sectionno=9C&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_9_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[9C. Presumption of culpable mental state.-- (1) In any prosecution for an offence under this Act`
  line `which requires a culpable mental state on the part of the accused, the Court shall presume the existence of`
  line `such mental state but it shall be a defence for the accused to prove the fact that he had no such mental state`
  line `with respect to the act charged as an offence in that prosecution.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In this section, "culpable mental state" includes intention, motive, knowledge of a fact,`
  line `and belief in, or reason to believe, a fact.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, a fact is said to be proved only when the Court believes it to exist`
  line `beyond reasonable doubt and not merely when its existence is established by a preponderance of`
  line probability.]
obj_root_law_sections_9_d:
  sectionId (71961)
  sectionNo 9D
  orderNo 21
  title `Relevancy of statements under certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 21.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71961&sectionno=9D&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_9_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[9D. Relevancy of statements under certain circumstances.-- (1) A statement made and signed by`
  line `a person before any Central Excise Officer of a gazetted rank during the course of any inquiry or proceeding`
  line `under this Act shall be relevant, for the purpose of proving, in any prosecution for an offence under this`
  line `Act, the truth of the facts which it contains,--`
  line
  line `(a) when the person who made the statement is dead or cannot be found, or is incapable of giving`
  line `evidence, or is kept out of the way by the adverse party, or whose presence cannot be obtained without`
  line `an amount of delay or expense which, under the circumstances of the case, the Court considers`
  line `unreasonable; or`
  line
  line `(b) when the person who made the statement is examined as a witness in the case before the Court`
  line `and the Court is of opinion that, having regard to the circumstances of the case, the statement should`
  line `be admitted in evidence in the interests of justice.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to any proceeding under`
  line `this Act, other than a proceeding before a Court, as they apply in relation to a proceeding before a Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_e:
  sectionId (72861)
  sectionNo 9E
  orderNo 22
  title `Application of Section 562 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898, and of the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72861&sectionno=9E&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_9_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[9E. Application of Section 562 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898, and of the Probation`
  line `of Offenders Act, 1958.-- (1) Nothing contained in Section 562 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)^2`
  line `, or in the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958 (20 of 1958), shall apply to a person convicted`
  line `of an offence under this Act unless that person is under eighteen years of age.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall have effect notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `sub-section (3) of Section 9.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 21.`
  line
  line `2. Now the relevant provisions of the CRPC, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (71963)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power of Courts to order forfeiture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71963&sectionno=10&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Any Court trying an offence under this Chapter may order`
  line `the forfeiture to ^1[Government] of any goods in respect of which the Court is satisfied that an offence under`
  line `this Chapter has been committed, and may also order the forfeiture of any receptacles, packages or`
  line `coverings in which such goods are contained and the animals, vehicles, vessels or other conveyances used`
  line `in carrying the goods, and any implements or machinery used in the manufacture of the goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (71964)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 24
  title `Recovery of sums due to Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71964&sectionno=11&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] In respect of duty and any other sums of any kind`
  line `payable to the Central Government under any of the provisions of this Act or of the rules made`
  line `thereunder ^2[including the amount required to be paid to the credit of the Central Government under Section`
  line `11-D], the officer empowered by the ^3[Central Board of Excise and Customs constituted under the Central`
  line `Boards of Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963)] to levy such duty or require the payment of such sums ^4[may`
  line `deduct or require any other Central Excise Officer or a proper officer referred to in Section 142 of the`
  line `Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) to deduct the amount so payable from any money owing to the person`
  line `from whom such sums may be recoverable or due which may be in his hands or under his disposal or control`
  line `or may be in the hands or under disposal or control of such other officer, or may recover the amount by`
  line `attachment and sale of excisable goods belonging to such person; and if the amount payable is not so`
  line `recovered he may prepare a certificate signed by him specifying the amount due from the person liable to`
  line `pay the same and send it to the Collector of the district in which such person resides or conducts his business`
  line `and the said Collector, on receipt of such certificate, shall proceed to recover from the said person the`
  line `amount specified therein as if it were an arrear of land revenue:`
  line
  line `^5[(2)(i) The Central Excise Officer may, by a notice in writing, require any other person from whom`
  line `money is due to such person, or may become due to such person, or who holds or may subsequently`
  line `hold money for or on account of such person, to pay to the credit of the Central Government either`
  line `forthwith upon the money becoming due or being held, or at or within the time specified in the notice,`
  line
  line `not being before the money becomes due or is held, so much of the money as is sufficient to pay the`
  line `amount due from such person or the whole of the money when it is equal to or less than that amount;`
  line
  line `(ii) every person to whom a notice is issued under this sub-section shall be bound to comply with`
  line `such notice, and in particular, where any such notice is issued to a post office, banking company or an`
  line `insurer, it shall not be necessary to produce any pass book, deposit receipt, policy or any other document`
  line `for the purpose of any entry, endorsement or the like being made before payment is made,`
  line `notwithstanding any rule, practice or requirement to the contrary;`
  line
  line `(iii) in a case where the person to whom a notice under this sub-section has been issued, fails to`
  line `make the payment in pursuance thereof to the Central Government, he shall be deemed to be a person`
  line `from whom duty and any other sums of any kind payable to the Central Government under any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder have become due, in respect of the amount specified`
  line `in the notice and all the consequences under this Act shall follow.]`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that where the person (hereinafter referred to as predecessor) from whom the duty or`
  line `any other sums of any kind, as specified in this section, is recoverable or due, transfers or otherwise`
  line `disposes of his business or trade in whole or in part, or effects any change in the ownership thereof, in`
  line `consequence of which he is succeeded in such business or trade by any other person, all excisable`
  line `goods, materials, preparations, plants, machineries, vessels, utensils, implements and articles in the`
  line `custody or possession of the person so succeeding may also be attached and sold by such officer`
  line `empowered by the Central Board of Excise and Customs, after obtaining written approval from`
  line `the ^7[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise, for the purposes`
  line `of recovering such duty or other sums recoverable or due from such predecessor at the time of such`
  line `transfer or otherwise disposal or change.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Renumbered sub-section (1) by Act 17 of 2013, s. 90.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 96.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 54 of 1963, s. 5 for "Central Board of Revenue" (w.e.f. 1-1-1964), here and throughout the Act.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 90(a) for "may deduct the amount so payable from any money owing to the person from whom`
  line `such sums may be recoverable or due which may be in his hands or under his disposal or control, or may recover the amount"`
  line `by Act 17 of 2013, s. 90(a).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 90(b)`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 80.`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (71965)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 25
  title `Recovery of duties not levied or not paid or short-levied or short-paid or erroneously refunded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71965&sectionno=11A&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[11A. Recovery of duties not levied or not paid or short-levied or short-paid or erroneously`
  line `refunded.-- (1) Where any duty of excise has not been levied or paid or has been short-levied or shortpaid or erroneously refunded, for any reason, other than the reason of fraud or collusion or any wilful`
  line `misstatement or suppression of facts or contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or of the rules`
  line `made thereunder with intent to evade payment of duty,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Excise Officer shall, within ^2[two years] from the relevant date, serve notice on the`
  line `person chargeable with the duty which has not been so levied or paid or which has been so short-levied`
  line `or short-paid or to whom the refund has erroneously been made, requiring him to show cause why he`
  line `should not pay the amount specified in the notice;`
  line
  line `(b) the person chargeable with duty may, before service of notice under clause (a), pay on the basis`
  line of,--
  line
  line `(i) his own ascertainment of such duty; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the duty ascertained by the Central Excise Officer,`
  line
  line `the amount of duty along with interest payable thereon under Section 11-AA.`
  line
  line `(2) The person who has paid the duty under clause (b) of sub-section (1), shall inform the Central Excise`
  line `Officer of such payment in writing, who, on receipt of such information, shall not serve any notice under`
  line `clause (a) of that sub-section in respect of the duty so paid or any penalty leviable under the provisions of`
  line `this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Central Excise Officer is of the opinion that the amount paid under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) falls short of the amount actually payable, then, he shall proceed to issue the notice as`
  line `provided for in clause (a) of that sub-section in respect of such amount which falls short of the amount`
  line `actually payable in the manner specified under that sub-section and the period of ^2[two years] shall be`
  line
  line `computed from the date of receipt of information under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Where any duty of excise has not been levied or paid or has been short-levied or short-paid or`
  line `erroneously refunded, by the reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) fraud; or`
  line
  line `(b) collusion; or`
  line
  line `(c) any wilful misstatement; or`
  line
  line `(d) suppression of facts; or`
  line
  line `(e) contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or of the rules made thereunder with intent to`
  line `evade payment of duty,`
  line
  line `by any person chargeable with the duty, the Central Excise Officer shall, within five years from the`
  line `relevant date, serve notice on such person requiring him to show cause why he should not pay the amount`
  line `specified in the notice along with interest payable thereon under Section 11-AA and a penalty equivalent`
  line `to the duty specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(5)`
  line `^3[* * *]`
  line
  line `(6)`
  line `^4[* * *]`
  line
  line `(7)`
  line `^5[* * *]`
  line
  line `^6[(7A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) or sub-section (4)`
  line ^7[*
  line `* *], the Central Excise Officer may, serve, subsequent to any notice or notices served under any of those`
  line `sub-sections, as the case may be, a statement, containing the details of duty of central excise not levied or`
  line `paid or short-levied or short-paid or erroneously refunded for the subsequent period, on the person`
  line `chargeable to duty of central excise, then, service of such statement shall be deemed to be service of notice`
  line `on such person under the aforesaid sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) ^7[* * *], subject to`
  line `the condition that the grounds relied upon for the subsequent period are the same as are mentioned in the`
  line `earlier notice or notices.]`
  line
  line `^8[(8) Where the service of notice is stayed by an order of a court or tribunal, the period of such stay`
  line `shall be excluded in computing the period of ^11[two years] referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1) or five`
  line `years referred to in sub-section (4)`
  line `^7[* * *], as the case may be.]`
  line
  line `(9) Where any appellate authority or tribunal or court concludes that the notice issued under`
  line `sub-section (4) is not sustainable for the reason that the charges of fraud or collusion or any wilful`
  line `misstatement or suppression of facts or contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or of the rules`
  line `made thereunder with intent to evade payment of duty has not been established against the person to whom`
  line `the notice was issued, the Central Excise Officer shall determine the duty of excise payable by such person`
  line `for the period of ^2[two years], deeming as if the notice were issued under clause (a) of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(10) The Central Excise Officer shall, after allowing the concerned person an opportunity of being`
  line `heard, and after considering the representation, if any, made by such person, determine the amount of duty`
  line `of excise due from such person not being in excess of the amount specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(11) The Central Excise Officer shall determine the amount of duty of excise under sub-section (10)--`
  line
  line `(a) within six months from the date of notice where it is possible to do so, in respect of cases falling`
  line `under sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) within ^2[two years from the date of notice, where it is possible to do so, in respect of cases`
  line `falling under sub-section (4)`
  line `^5[* * *].`
  line
  line `(12) Where the appellate authority or tribunal or court modifies the amount of duty of excise determined`
  line `by the Central Excise Officer under sub-section (10), then the amount of penalties and interest under this`
  line `section shall stand modified accordingly, taking into account the amount of duty of excise so modified.`
  line
  line `(13) Where the amount as modified by the appellate authority or tribunal or court is more than the`
  line `amount determined under sub-section (10) by the Central Excise Officer, the time within which the interest`
  line `or penalty is payable under this Act shall be counted from the date of the order of the appellate authority or`
  line `tribunal or court in respect of such increased amount.`
  line
  line `(14) Where an order determining the duty of excise is passed by the Central Excise Officer under this`
  line `section, the person liable to pay the said duty of excise shall pay the amount so determined along with the`
  line `interest due on such amount whether or not the amount of interest is specified separately.`
  line
  line `(15) The provisions of sub-sections (1) to (14) shall apply, mutatis mutandis, to the recovery of interest`
  line `where interest payable has not been paid or part paid or erroneously refunded.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1. For the purposes of this section and Section 11-AC,--`
  line
  line `(a) dbqysrefund" includes rebate of duty of excise on excisable goods exported out of India or on`
  line `excisable materials used in the manufacture of goods which are exported out of India;`
  line `(b) "relevant date" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of excisable goods on which duty of excise has not been levied or paid or has`
  line `been short-levied or short-paid, and no periodical return as required by the provisions of this Act`
  line `has been filed, the last date on which such return is required to be filed under this Act and the rules`
  line `made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of excisable goods on which duty of excise has not been levied or paid or has`
  line `been short-levied or short-paid and the return has been filed ^9[* * *], the date on which such return`
  line `has been filed;`
  line
  line `(iii) in any other case, the date on which duty of excise is required to be paid under this Act or`
  line `the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(iv) in a case where duty of excise is provisionally assessed under this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder, the date of adjustment of duty after the final assessment thereof;`
  line
  line `(v) in the case of excisable goods on which duty of excise has been erroneously refunded, the`
  line `date of such refund;`
  line
  line `^10[(vi) in the case where only interest is to be recovered, the date of payment of duty to which`
  line `such interest relates.]`
  line
  line `(c)`
  line `^11[* * *]`
  line
  line `^12[Explanation 2.-- For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any non-levy, short-levy,`
  line `non-payment, short-payment or erroneous refund where no show cause notice has been issued before the`
  line `date on which the Finance Bill, 2015 receives the assent of the President, shall be governed by the provisions`
  line `of Section 11A as amended by the Finance Act, 2015.]`
  line
  line `^13[(16) The provisions of this section shall not apply to a case where the liability of duty not paid or`
  line `short-paid is self-assessed and declared as duty payable by the assessee in the periodic returns filed by him,`
  line `and in such case, recovery of non-payment or short-payment of duty shall be made in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 63.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 143, for "one year".`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (5) omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 93(i).`
  line
  line `4. Sub-section (6) omitted by ibid, s. 93(i).`
  line
  line `5. Sub-section (7) omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 93(i).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 91.`
  line
  line `7. The words "or sub-section (5)" omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 93(ii).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 135(b), for sub-section 8.`
  line
  line `9. The words "on due date" omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 93(iii)(A).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by ibid, s. 93(iii)(B).`
  line
  line `11. Clause (c) omitted by ibid, s. 93(iii)(C)..`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 93(iv).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by ibid, s. 93(iv).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_aa:
  sectionId (71966)
  sectionNo 11AA
  orderNo 26
  title `Interest on delayed payment of duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_aa_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 64, for Section 11-AA and 11-AB.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71966&sectionno=11AA&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_11_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[11AA. Interest on delayed payment of duty.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `judgment, decree, order or direction of the Appellate Tribunal or any court or in any other provision of this`
  line `Act or the rules made thereunder, the person, who is liable to pay duty, shall, in addition to the duty, be`
  line `liable to pay interest at the rate specified in sub-section (2), whether such payment is made voluntarily or`
  line `after determination of the amount of duty under Section 11A.`
  line
  line `(2) Interest, at such rate not below ten per cent, and not exceeding thirty-six per cent per annum, as the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, fix, shall be paid in terms of`
  line `Section 11A after the due date by the person liable to pay duty and such interest shall be calculated from`
  line `the date on which such duty becomes due up to the date of actual payment of the amount due.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), no interest shall be payable where,--`
  line
  line `(a) the duty becomes payable consequent to the issue of an order, instruction or direction by the`
  line `Board under Section 37-B; and`
  line
  line `(b) such amount of duty is voluntarily paid in full, within forty-five days from the date of issue of`
  line `such order, instruction or direction, without reserving any right to appeal against the said payment at`
  line `any subsequent stage of such payment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_ac:
  sectionId (71967)
  sectionNo 11AC
  orderNo 27
  title `Penalty for short-levy or non-levy of duty in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_ac_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 94, for "11-AC".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71967&sectionno=11AC&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_11_ac_content:
  string
  line `^1[11AC. Penalty for short-levy or non-levy of duty in certain cases.-- (1) The amount of penalty`
  line `for non-levy or short-levy or non-payment or short-payment or erroneous refund shall be as follows--`
  line
  line `(a) where any duty of excise has not been levied or paid or has been short-levied or short-paid or`
  line `erroneously refunded, for any reason other than the reason of fraud or collusion or any wilful`
  line `mis-statement or suppression of facts or contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or of the`
  line `rules made thereunder with intent to evade payment of duty, the person who is liable to pay duty as determined under sub-section (10) of Section 11-A shall also be liable to pay a penalty not exceeding`
  line `ten per cent of the duty so determined or Rupees Five thousand, whichever is higher:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such duty and interest payable under Section 11-AA is paid either before`
  line `the issue of show cause notice or within thirty days of issue of show cause notice, no penalty shall`
  line `be payable by the person liable to pay duty or the person who has paid the duty and all proceedings`
  line `in respect of said duty and interest shall be deemed to be concluded;`
  line
  line `(b) where any duty as determined under sub-section (10) of Section 11A and the interest payable`
  line `thereon under Section 11AA in respect of transactions referred to in clause (a) is paid within thirty days`
  line `of the date of communication of the order of the Central Excise Officer who has determined such duty,`
  line `the amount of penalty liable to be paid by such person shall be twenty-five per cent of the penalty`
  line `imposed, subject to the condition that such reduced penalty is also paid within the period so specified;`
  line
  line `(c) where any duty of excise has not been levied or paid or has been short-levied or short-paid or`
  line `erroneously refunded, by reason of fraud or collusion or any wilful misstatement or suppression of`
  line `facts, or contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or of the rules made thereunder with intent`
  line `to evade payment of duty, the person who is liable to pay duty as determined under sub-section (10) of`
  line `Section 11A shall also be liable to pay a penalty equal to the duty so determined:`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of the cases where the details relating to such transactions are recorded`
  line `in the specified record for the period beginning with the 8th April, 2011 up to the date on which`
  line `the Finance Bill, 2015 receives the assent of the President (both days inclusive), the penalty shall`
  line `be fifty per cent of the duty so determined;`
  line
  line `(d) where any duty demanded in a show cause notice and the interest payable thereon under`
  line `Section 11AA, issued in respect of transactions referred to in clause (c), is paid within thirty days of`
  line `the communication of show cause notice, the amount of penalty liable to be paid by such person shall`
  line `be fifteen per cent. of the duty demanded, subject to the condition that such reduced penalty is also paid`
  line `within the period so specified and all proceedings in respect of the said duty, interest and penalty shall`
  line `be deemed to be concluded;`
  line
  line `(e) where any duty as determined under sub-section (10) of Section 11A and the interest payable`
  line `thereon under Section 11AA in respect of transactions referred to in clause (c) is paid within thirty days`
  line `of the date of communication of the order of the Central Excise Officer who has determined such duty,`
  line `the amount of penalty liable to be paid by such person shall be twenty-five per cent of the duty so`
  line `determined, subject to the condition that such reduced penalty is also paid within the period so specified.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the appellate authority or tribunal or court modifies the amount of duty of excise determined`
  line `by the Central Excise Officer under sub-section (10) of Section 11A, then, the amount of penalty payable`
  line `under clause (c) of sub-section (1) and the interest payable under Section 11AA shall stand modified`
  line `accordingly and after taking into account the amount of duty of excise so modified, the person who is liable to pay duty as determined under sub-section (10) of Section 11A shall also be liable to pay such amount of`
  line `penalty and interest so modified.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the amount of duty or penalty is increased by the appellate authority or tribunal or court over`
  line `the amount determined under sub-section (10) of Section 11A by the Central Excise Officer, the time within`
  line `which the interest and the reduced penalty is payable under clause (b) or clause (e) of sub-section (1) in`
  line `relation to such increased amount of duty shall be counted from the date of the order of the appellate`
  line `authority or tribunal or court.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.-- For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that--`
  line
  line `(i) any case of non-levy, short-levy, non-payment, short-payment or erroneous refund where no`
  line `show cause notice has been issued before the date on which the Finance Bill, 2015 receives the assent`
  line `of the President shall be governed by the provisions of Section 11AC as amended by the Finance Act,`
  line 2015;
  line
  line `(ii) any case of non-levy, short-levy, non-payment, short-payment or erroneous refund where show`
  line `cause notice has been issued but an order determining duty under sub-section (10) of Section 11-A has`
  line `not been passed before the date on which the Finance Bill, 2015 receives the assent of the President,`
  line `shall be eligible to closure of proceedings on payment of duty and interest under the proviso to`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) or on payment of duty, interest and penalty under clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (1), subject to the condition that the payment of duty, interest and penalty, as the case may`
  line `be, is made within thirty days from the date on which the Finance Bill, 2015 receives the assent of the`
  line President;
  line
  line `(iii) any case of non-levy, short-levy, non-payment, short-payment or erroneous refund where an`
  line `order determining duty under sub-section (10) of Section 11-A is passed after the date on which the`
  line `Finance Bill, 2015 receives the assent of the President shall be eligible to payment of reduced penalty`
  line `under clause (b) or clause (e) of sub-section (1), subject to the condition that the payment of duty,`
  line `interest and penalty is made within thirty days of the communication of the order.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.-- For the purposes of this section, the expression "specified records" means records`
  line `maintained by the person chargeable with the duty in accordance with any law for the time being in force`
  line `and includes computerised records.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_b:
  sectionId (71968)
  sectionNo 11B
  orderNo 28
  title `Claim for refund of duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71968&sectionno=11B&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[11B. Claim for refund of ^2[duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty].-- (1) Any person`
  line `claiming refund of any ^3[duty of excise and interest, if any, paid on such duty] may make an application for`
  line `refund of such ^2[duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty] to the Assistant ^4[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] ^5[or Deputy ^6[Principal Commissioner of Central`
  line `Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] before the expiry of ^7[two years] ^8[from the relevant date] ^9[in`
  line `such form ^10[and manner]] as may be prescribed and the application shall be accompanied by such`
  line `documentary or other evidence (including the documents referred to in Section 12-A) as the applicant may`
  line `furnish to establish that the amount of ^3[duty of excise and interest, if any, paid on such duty] in relation to`
  line `which such refund is claimed was collected from, or paid by, him and the incidence of such ^2[duty and`
  line `interest, if any, paid on such duty had not been passed on by him to any other person:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an application for refund has been made before the commencement of the`
  line `Central Excises and Customs Laws (Amendment) Act, 1991, such application shall be deemed to have`
  line `been made under this sub-section as amended by the said Act and the same shall be dealt with in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2) as substituted by that Act:]`
  line
  line `^12[Provided further that] the limitation of ^7[two years] shall not apply where any ^2[duty and interest,`
  line `if any, paid on such duty] has been paid under protest.`
  line
  line `^13[* * *]`
  line
  line `^14[(2) If, on receipt of any such application, the Assistant ^6[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise`
  line `or Commissioner of Central Excise[ ^15[or Deputy ^6[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise]] is satisfied that the whole or any part of the ^3[duty of excise and interest,`
  line `if any, paid on such duty] paid by the applicant is refundable, he may make an order accordingly and the`
  line `amount so determined shall be credited to the Fund:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of ^3[duty of excise and interest, if any, paid on such duty] as determined`
  line `by the Assistant ^6[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excisec]`
  line
  line `^15[or Deputy ^6[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise]] under`
  line `the foregoing provisions of this sub-section shall, instead of being credited to the Fund, be paid to the`
  line `applicant, if such amount is relatable to--`
  line
  line `(a) rebate of duty of excise on excisable goods exported out of India or on excisable materials used`
  line `in the manufacture of goods which are exported out of India;`
  line
  line `(b) unspent advance deposits lying in balance in the applicant's account current maintained with`
  line `the ^16[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise];`
  line
  line `(c) refund of credit of duty paid on excisable goods used as inputs in accordance with the rules`
  line `made, or any notification issued, under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the ^17[duty of excise and interest, if any paid on such duty paid by the manufacturer, if he had`
  line `not passed on the incidence of such ^18[duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty] to any other person;`
  line
  line `(e) the ^17[duty of excise and interest, if any paid on such duty borne by the buyer, if he had not`
  line `passed on the incidence of such ^18[duty and interest, if any, paid on such duty to any other person;`
  line
  line `(f) the ^17[duty of excise and interest, if any paid on such duty borne by any other such class of`
  line `applicants as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no notification under clause (f) of the first proviso shall be issued unless`
  line `in the opinion of the Central Government the incidence of ^18[duty and interest, if any, paid on such`
  line `duty] has not been passed on by the persons concerned to any other person.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any judgment, decree, order or direction of`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal or any Court or in any other provision of this Act or the rules made thereunder or`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, no refund shall be made except as provided in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Every notification under clause (f) of the first proviso to sub-section (2) shall be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament, if it is sitting, as soon as may be after the issue of the notification, and, if it is not`
  line `sitting, within seven days of its reassembly, and the Central Government shall seek the approval of`
  line `Parliament to the notification by a resolution moved within a period of fifteen days beginning with the day`
  line `on which the notification is so laid before the House of the People and if Parliament makes any modification`
  line `in the notification or directs that the notification should cease to have effect, the notification shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, but without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done thereunder.`
  line
  line `(5) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any notification issued under clause (f) of the`
  line `first proviso to sub-section (2), including any such notification approved or modified under sub-section (4),`
  line `may be rescinded by the Central Government at any time by notification in the Official Gazette.]`
  line
  line `^19[Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(A) "refund" includes rebate of duty of excise on excisable goods exported out of India or on`
  line `excisable materials used in the manufacture of goods which are exported out of India;`
  line
  line `(B) "relevant date" means,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of goods exported out of India where a refund of excise duty paid is available in`
  line `respect of the goods themselves or, as the case may be, the excisable materials used in the`
  line `manufacture of such goods,--`
  line
  line `(i) if the goods are exported by sea or air, the date on which the ship or the aircraft in which`
  line `such goods are loaded, leaves India, or`
  line
  line `(ii) if the goods are exported by land, the date on which such goods pass the frontier, or`
  line
  line `(iii) if the goods are exported by post, the date of despatch of goods by the Post Office`
  line `concerned to a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of goods returned for being remade, refined, reconditioned, or subjected to any other`
  line `similar process, in any factory, the date of entry into the factory for the purposes aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of goods to which banderols are required to be affixed if removed for home`
  line `consumption but not so required when exported outside India, if returned to a factory after having been`
  line `removed from such factory for export out of India, the date of entry into the factory;`
  line
  line `(d) in a case where a manufacturer is required to pay a sum, for a certain period, on the basis of the`
  line `rate fixed by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette in full discharge of his`
  line `liability for the duty leviable on his production of certain goods, if after the manufacturer has made the`
  line `payment on the basis of such rate for any period but before the expiry of that period such rate is reduced,`
  line `the date of such reduction;`
  line
  line `^20[(e) in the case of a person, other than the manufacturer, the date of purchase of the goods by such`
  line person;]
  line
  line `^21[(ea) in the case of goods which are exempt from payment of duty by a special order issued under`
  line `sub-section (2) of Section 5-A, the date of issue of such order;]`
  line
  line `^22[(eb) in case where duty of excise is paid provisionally under this Act or the rules made thereunder,`
  line `the date of adjustment of duty after the final assessment thereof;]`
  line
  line `^23[(ec) in case where the duty becomes refundable as a consequence of judgment, decree, order or`
  line `direction of appellate authority, Appellate Tribunal or any court, the date of such judgment, decree,`
  line `order or direction;]`
  line
  line `(f) in any other case, the date of payment of duty.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 1978, s. 21, (w.e.f. 1-8-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 80(i)(b), for "duty" (w.e.f. 10-5-2008).`
