  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 3(b) (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 74.`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 80(i)(a), for "duty of excise".`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by ibid, s. 80(i)(b), for "duty".`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 3 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `13. Explanation to sub-section (1) omitted by Act 44 of 1980, s. 49.`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 3 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `15. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 119.`
  line
  line `16. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `17. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 80(ii)(a), for "duty of excise".`
  line
  line `18. Subs. by ibid, s. 80(ii)(b), for "duty".`
  line
  line `19. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 49, for the Explanation.`
  line
  line `20. Subs. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 3(c), for sub clause (e) (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `21. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 77.`
  line
  line `22. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 108.`
  line
  line `23. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 117.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_bb:
  sectionId (71970)
  sectionNo 11BB
  orderNo 29
  title `Interest on delayed refunds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_bb_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_bb_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71970&sectionno=11BB&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_11_bb_content:
  string
  line `^1[11-BB. Interest on delayed refunds.-- If any duty ordered to be refunded under sub-section (2) of Section 11-B to any applicant is not refunded within three months from the date of receipt of application under sub-section (1) of that section, there shall be paid to that applicant interest at such rate, ^2[not below five per cent and not exceeding thirty per cent per annum as is for the time being fixed ^3[by the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette,]] on such duty from the date immediately after the expiry of three months from the date of receipt of such application till the date of refund of such duty:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any duty ordered to be refunded under sub-section (2) of Section 11-B in respect of an application under sub-section (1) of that section made before the date on which the Finance Bill, 1995 receives the assent of the President, is not refunded within three months from such date, there shall be paid to the applicant interest under this section from the date immediately after three months from such date, till the date of refund of such duty.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- Where any order of refund is made by the Commissioner (Appeals), Appellate Tribunal ^4[National Tax Tribunal] or any court against an order of the Assistant ^5[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] ^6[or Deputy ^5[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise]], under sub-section (2) of Section 11-B, the order passed by the Commissioner (Appeals), Appellate Tribunal ^4[National Tax Tribunal] or, as the case may be, by the court shall be deemed to be an order passed under the said sub-section (2) for the purposes of this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_bb_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 75.`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 126, for "not below ten per cent" (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 102, for "by the Board".`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and Sch. (Pt. VII) (w.e.f. 28-12-2005).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 119.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_c:
  sectionId (71971)
  sectionNo 11C
  orderNo 30
  title `Power not to recover duty of excise not levied or short-levied as a result of general practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71971&sectionno=11C&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_11_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[11C. Power not to recover duty of excise not levied or short-levied as a result of general`
  line `practice.--- ^2[(1)] Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, if the Central Government is satisfied--`
  line
  line `(a) that a practice was, or is, generally prevalent regarding levy of duty of excise (including nonlevy thereof) on any excisable goods; and`
  line
  line `(b) that such goods were, or are, liable--`
  line
  line `(i) to duty of excise, in cases where according to the said practice the duty was not, or is not`
  line `being, levied, or`
  line
  line `(ii) to a higher amount of duty of excise than what was, or is being, levied, according to the`
  line `said practice,`
  line `then, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette direct that the whole of the`
  line `duty of excise payable on such goods, or, as the case may be, the duty of excise in excess of that payable on such goods, but for the said practice, shall not be required to be paid in respect of the goods on which`
  line `the duty of excise was not, or is not being, levied, or was, or is being, short-levied, in accordance with the`
  line `said practice.]`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Where any notification under sub-section (1) in respect of any goods has been issued, the whole`
  line `of the duty of excise paid on such goods or, as the case may be, the duty of excise paid in excess of that`
  line `payable on such goods, which would not have been paid if the said notification had been in force, shall be`
  line `dealt with in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2) of Section 11-B:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person claiming the refund of such duty or, as the case may be, excess duty, makes`
  line `an application in this behalf to the Assistant ^4[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise] ^5[or Deputy ^4[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise]], in the form referred to in sub-section (1) of Section 11-B, before`
  line `the expiry of six months from the date of issue of the said notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 1978, s. 21, (w.e.f. 1-7-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Renumbered as sub-sec. (1) and sub-sec. (2) inserted by Act 29 of 1988, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-7-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 4, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 119.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_d:
  sectionId (71972)
  sectionNo 11D
  orderNo 31
  title `Duties of excise collected from the buyer to be deposited with the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71972&sectionno=11D&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_11_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[11D. Duties of excise collected from the buyer to be deposited with the Central Government.--`
  line
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any order or direction of the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `or any Court or in any other provision of this Act or the rules made thereunder, ^2[every person who is liable`
  line `to pay duty under this Act or the rules made thereunder, and has collected any amount in excess of the duty`
  line `assessed or determined and paid on any excisable goods under this Act or the rules made thereunder from`
  line `the buyer of such goods in any manner as representing duty of excise, shall forthwith pay the amount so`
  line `collected to the credit of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) Every person, who has collected any amount in excess of the duty assessed or determined and`
  line `paid on any excisable goods or has collected any amount as representing duty of excise on any excisable`
  line `goods which are wholly exempt or are chargeable to nil rate of duty from any person in any manner, shall`
  line `forthwith pay the amount so collected to the credit of the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Where any amount is required to be paid to the credit of the Central Government under ^5[subsection (1) or sub-section (1-A), as the case may be,] and which has not been so paid, the Central Excise`
  line `Officer may serve, on the person liable to pay such amount, a notice requiring him to show cause why the`
  line `said amount, as specified in the notice, should not be paid by him to the credit of the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Excise Officer shall, after considering the representation, if any, made by the person`
  line `on whom the notice is served under sub-section (2), determine the amount due from such person (not being`
  line `in excess of the amount specified in the notice) and thereupon such person shall pay the amount so`
  line determined.
  line
  line `(4) The amount paid to the credit of the Central Government under ^6[sub-section (1) or sub-section`
  line `(1A) or sub-section (3), as the case may be, shall be adjusted against the duty of excise payable by the`
  line `person on finalisation of assessment or any other proceeding for determination of the duty of excise relating`
  line `to the excisable goods referred to in ^7[sub-section (1) and sub-section (1A)].`
  line
  line `(5) Where any surplus is left after the adjustment under sub-section (4), the amount of such surplus`
  line `shall either be credited to the Fund or, as the case may be, refunded to the person who has borne the`
  line `incidence of such amount, in accordance with the provisions of Section 11B and such person may make an`
  line `application under that section in such cases within six months from the date of the public notice to be issued`
  line `by the Assistant ^8[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise for the`
  line `refund of such surplus amount.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 5 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 103, for certain words (w.r.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 81(i).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 103, for sub-section (2) (w.r.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 81(ii), for the word, brackets and figure "sub-section (1)".`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 81(iii)(a), for the word, brackets and figure “sub-section (1) or sub-section (3)".`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by ibid, s. 81(iii)(b), for the word, brackets and figure "sub-section (1)".`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for dnqtsCommissioner of Central Excise".`
obj_root_law_sections_11_dd:
  sectionId (71973)
  sectionNo 11DD
  orderNo 32
  title `Interest on the amounts collected in excess of the duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_dd_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_dd_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71973&sectionno=11DD&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_11_dd_content:
  string
  line `^[11DD. Interest on the amounts collected in excess of the duty.-- (1) Where an amount has been`
  line `collected in excess of the duty assessed or determined and paid on any excisable goods under this Act or`
  line `the rules made thereunder from the ^2[buyer of such goods or from any person or where a person has`
  line `collected any amount as representing duty of excise on any excisable goods which are wholly exempt or`
  line `are chargeable to nil rate of duty, the person who is liable to pay such amount as determined under`
  line `sub-section (3) of Section 11-D, shall, in addition to the amount, be liable to pay interest at such rate not`
  line `below ten per cent, and not exceeding thirty-six percent per annum, as is for the time being fixed by the`
  line `Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, from the first day of the month succeeding the`
  line `month in which the amount ought to have been paid under this Act, but for the provisions contained in`
  line `sub-section (3) of Section 11-D, till the date of payment of such amount:`
  line
  line `Provided that in such cases where the amount becomes payable consequent to issue of an order,`
  line `instruction or direction by the Board under Section 37B, and such amount payable is voluntarily paid`
  line `in full, without reserving any right to appeal against such payment at any subsequent stage, within`
  line `forty-five days from the date of issue of such order, instruction or direction, as the case may be, no`
  line `interest shall be payable and in other cases the interest shall be payable on the whole amount, including`
  line `the amount already paid.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply to cases where the amount had become payable or`
  line `ought to have been paid before the day on which the Finance Bill, 2003 receives the assent of the President.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.-- Where the amount determined under sub-section (3) of Section 11-D is reduced by`
  line `the Commissioner (Appeals), the Appellate Tribunal or, as the case may be, the court, the interest payable`
  line `thereon under sub-section (1) shall be on such reduced amount.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--Where the amount determined under sub-section (3) of Section 11-D is increased by`
  line `the Commissioner (Appeals), the Appellate Tribunal or, as the case may be, the court, the interest payable`
  line `thereon under sub-section (1) shall be on such increased amount.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_dd_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 140 (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 82, for the words "buyer of such goods, the person".`
obj_root_law_sections_11_dda:
  sectionId (71974)
  sectionNo 11DDA
  orderNo 33
  title `Provisional attachment to protect revenue in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_dda_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_dda_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71974&sectionno=11DDA&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_11_dda_content:
  string
  line `^1[11DDA. Provisional attachment to protect revenue in certain cases.-- (1) Where, during the`
  line `pendency of any proceedings under Section 11A or Section 11D, the Central Excise Officer is of the opinion`
  line `that for the purpose of protecting the interests of revenue, it is necessary so to do, he may, with the previous`
  line `approval of the ^1[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise], by order`
  line `in writing, attach provisionally any property belonging to the person on whom notice is served under ^3[* *`
  line `*] Section 11A or sub-section (2) of Section 11D, as the case may be, in accordance with the rules made in`
  line `this behalf under Section 142 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962).`
  line
  line `(2) Every such provisional attachment shall cease to have effect after the expiry of a period of six`
  line `months from the date of the order made under sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^4[Principal Chief Commissioner of Central Excise or Chief Commissioner of`
  line `Central Excise] may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the aforesaid period by such further`
  line `period or periods as he thinks fit, so, however, that the total period of extension shall not in any case`
  line `exceed two years:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where an application for settlement of case under Section 32-E is made to the`
  line `Settlement Commission, the period commencing from the date on which such application is made and`
  line `ending with the date on which an order under sub-section (1) of Section 32-F is made shall be excluded`
  line `from the period specified in the preceding proviso.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_dda_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 36.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `3. The words "sub-section (1) of" omitted by Act 17 of 2013, s. 92.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Chief Commissioner of Central Excise".`
obj_root_law_sections_11_e:
  sectionId (71975)
  sectionNo 11E
  orderNo 34
  title `Liability under Act to be first charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 66.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71975&sectionno=11E&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_11_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[11E. Liability under Act to be first charge.-- Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained`
  line `in any Central Act or State Act, any amount of duty, penalty, interest, or any other sum payable by an`
  line `assessee or any other person under this Act or the rules made thereunder shall, save as otherwise provided`
  line `in Section 529A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), the Recovery of Debts Due to Banks and the Financial Institutions Act, 1993 (51 of 1993) ^1[the Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets`
  line `and the Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002) and the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code,`
  line `2016], be the first charge on the property of the assessee or the person, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (71976)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 35
  title `Application of the provisions of Act 52 of 1962 to Central Excise Duties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71976&sectionno=12&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `12. Application of the provisions of Act ^1[52 of 1962] to Central Excise Duties.-- The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that any of the provisions of the ^2[Customs`
  line `Act, 1962 (52 of 1962)], relating to the levy of and exemption from customs duties, drawback of duty,`
  line `warehousing, offences and penalties, confiscation, and procedure relating to offences and appeals shall,`
  line `with such modifications and alterations as it may consider necessary or desirable to adapt them to the`
  line `circumstances, be applicable in regard to like matters in respect of the duties imposed by`
  line `Section 3 ^3[Section 3-A]:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that the provisions of the Customs Act, 1962(52 of 1962) relating to offences and penalties`
  line `shall not apply for the matters covered by section 3A for the period beginning on the 10th day of May, 2008`
  line `and ending immediately before the day on which the Finance Bill, 2011 receives the assent of the President.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 78,`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by ibid, s. 78, for "Sea Customs Act, 1878 (8 of 1878)".`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 67 (w.r.e.f. 10-5-2008).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by ibid, s. 67 (w.e.f. 10-5-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (71977)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 36
  title `Price of goods to indicate the amount of duty paid thereon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 6 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71977&sectionno=12A&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Price of goods to indicate the amount of duty paid thereon.-- Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force, every person who is liable to pay duty of`
  line `excise on any goods shall, at the time of clearance of the goods, prominently indicate in all the documents`
  line `relating to assessment, sales invoice, and other like documents, the amount of such duty which will form`
  line `part of the price at which such goods are to be sold.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_b:
  sectionId (71978)
  sectionNo 12B
  orderNo 37
  title `Presumption that the incidence of duty has been passed on to the buyer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 6 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71978&sectionno=12B&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[12B. Presumption that the incidence of duty has been passed on to the buyer.-- Every person who`
  line `has paid the duty of excise on any goods under this Act shall, unless the contrary is proved by him, be`
  line `deemed to have passed on the full incidence of such duty to the buyer of such goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_c:
  sectionId (71979)
  sectionNo 12C
  orderNo 38
  title `Consumer Welfare Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71979&sectionno=12C&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_12_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[12C. Consumer Welfare Fund.-- (1) There shall be established by the Central Government a fund,`
  line `to be called the Consumer Welfare Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be credited to the Fund, in such manner as may be prescribed,--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of duty of excise referred to in sub-section (2) of Section 11B or sub-section (2) of`
  line `Section 11C or sub-section (2) of Section 11D;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of duty of customs referred to in sub-section (2) of Section 27 or sub-section (2) of`
  line `Section 28A, or sub-section (2) of Section 28B of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962);`
  line
  line `(c) any income from investment of the amount credited to the Fund and any other monies received`
  line `by the Central Government for the purposes of this Fund;`
  line
  line `^2](d) the surplus amount referred to in sub-section (6) of Section 73A of the Finance Act, 1994 (32`
  line `of 1994).]]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 6 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 64.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_d:
  sectionId (71980)
  sectionNo 12D
  orderNo 39
  title `Utilisation of the Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_d_content
  footnotes `6. Ins. by Act 40 of 1991, s. 6 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71980&sectionno=12D&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_12_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[12D. Utilisation of the Fund.-- (1) Any money credited to the Fund shall be utilised by the Central`
  line `Government for the welfare of the consumers in accordance with such rules as that Government may make`
  line `in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall maintain or, if it thinks fit, specify the authority which shall maintain,`
  line `proper and separate account and other relevant records in relation to the Fund in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_e:
  sectionId (71981)
  sectionNo 12E
  orderNo 40
  title `Powers of Central Excise Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71981&sectionno=12E&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_12_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[^2[12E.] Powers of Central Excise Officers.---(1) A Central Excise Officer may exercise the powers`
  line `and discharge the duties conferred or imposed under this Act on any other Central Excise Officer who is`
  line `subordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the ^3[Principal Commissioner of Central`
  line `Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] (Appeals) shall not exercise the powers and discharge the duties`
  line `conferred or imposed on a Central Excise Officer other than those specified in Section 14 or Chapter VIA.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 79 of 1985, s. 4 (w.e.f. 27-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Section "12A" renumbered as "12E" by Act 40 of 1991, s. 7 (w.e.f. 20-9-1991).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
obj_root_law_sections_12_f:
  sectionId (71982)
  sectionNo 12F
  orderNo 41
  title `Power of search and seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_f_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_f_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71982&sectionno=12F&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_12_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[12F. Power of search and seizure.-- (1) Where the Joint ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central`
  line `Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] or Additional ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise] or such other Central Excise Officer as may be notified by the Board has`
  line `reasons to believe that any goods liable to confiscation or any documents or books or things, which in his`
  line `opinion shall be useful for or relevant to any proceedings under this Act, are secreted in any place, he may authorise in writing any Central Excise Officer to search and seize or may himself search and seize such`
  line `documents or books or things.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), relating to search and seizure`
  line `shall, so far as may be, apply to search and seizure under this section subject to the modification that`
  line `sub-section (5) of Section 165 of the said Code shall have effect as if for the word "Magistrate", wherever`
  line `it occurs, the words "^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise]"`
  line `were substituted.""`
obj_root_law_sections_12_f_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 68.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 137, for sub-section (2)`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (71983)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 42
  title `Power to arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71983&sectionno=13&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[13. Power to arrest.--- Any Central Excise Officer not below the rank of Inspector of Central Excise`
  line `may, with the prior approval of the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central`
  line `Excise], arrest any person whom he has reason to believe to be liable to punishment under this Act or the`
  line `rules made thereunder.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any person accused or reasonably suspected of committing an offence under this Act or any rules`
  line `made thereunder, who on demand of any officer duly empowered by the Central Government in this behalf`
  line `refuses to give his name and residence, or who gives a name or residence which such officer has reason to`
  line `believe to be false, may be arrested by such officer in order that his name and residence may be ascertained.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 141, for section 13 (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (71984)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to summon persons to give evidence and produce documents in inquiries under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71984&sectionno=14&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Central Excise Officer duly empowered by the Central Government in this behalf shall have`
  line `power to summon any person whose attendance he considers necessary either to give evidence or to produce`
  line `a document or any other thing in any inquiry which such officer is making for any of the purposes of this`
  line `Act. A summons to produce documents or other things may be for the production of certain specified`
  line `documents or things or for the production of all documents or things of a certain description in the`
  line `possession or under the control of the person summoned.`
  line
  line `(2) All persons so summoned shall be bound to attend, either in person or by an authorised agent, as`
  line `such officer may direct; and all persons so summoned shall be bound to state the truth upon any subject`
  line `respecting which they are examined or make statements and to produce such documents and other things`
  line `as may be required:`
  line
  line `Provided that the exemptions under Sections 132 and 133 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5`
  line `of 1908) shall be applicable to requisitions of attendance under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) Every such inquiry as aforesaid shall be deemed to be a "judicial proceeding" within the meaning`
  line `of Section 193 and Section 228 of the Indian Penal Code, 1860 (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (71985)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 44
  title `Special audit in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71985&sectionno=14A&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[14A. Special audit in certain cases.-- (1) If at any stage of enquiry, investigation or any other`
  line `proceedings before him, any Central Excise Officer not below the rank of an Assistant ^2[Principal`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise], having regard to the nature and`
  line `complexity of the case and the interest of revenue, is of the opinion that the value has not been correctly`
  line `declared or determined by a manufacturer or any person, he may, with the previous approval of`
  line `the ^3[Principal Chief Commissioner of Central Excise or Chief Commissioner of Central Excise, direct`
  line `such manufacturer or such person to get the accounts of his factory, office, depots, distributors or any other`
  line `place, as may be specified by the said Central Excise Officer, audited by a ^4[cost accountant or chartered`
  line `accountant, nominated by the ^3[Principal Chief Commissioner of Central Excise or Chief Commissioner`
  line `of Central Excise in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^4[cost accountant or chartered accountant, so nominated shall, within the period specified by`
  line `the Central Excise Officer, submit a report of such audit duly signed and certified by him to the said Central`
  line `Excise Officer mentioning therein such other particulars as may be specified:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Excise Officer may, on an application made to him in this behalf by the`
  line `manufacturer or the person and for any material and sufficient reason, extend the said period by such`
  line `further period or periods as he thinks fit; so, however, that the aggregate of the period originally fixed`
  line `and the period or periods so extended shall not, in any case, exceed one hundred and eighty days from`
  line `the date on which the direction under sub-section (1) is received by the manufacturer or the person.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall have effect notwithstanding that the accounts of the`
  line `manufacturer or person aforesaid have been audited under any other law for the time being in force or`
  line otherwise.
  line
  line `(4)`
  line `^5[* * *]`
  line
  line `(5) The manufacturer or the person shall be given an opportunity of being heard in respect of any`
  line `material gathered on the basis of audit under sub-section (1) and proposed to be utilised in any proceedings`
  line `under this Act or rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `^6[Explanation 1].-- For the purpose of this section, cost accountant shall have the meaning assigned`
  line `to it in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of Section 2 of the Cost and Works Accountants Act, 1959 (23 of`
  line `1959).]`
  line
  line `^7[Explanation 2.-- For the purposes of this section, "chartered accountant" shall have the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of Section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of`
  line `1949).ic963]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 76 (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by ibid, s. 95, for "Chief Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 105(i), for "cost accountant".`
  line
  line `5. Omitted by Act 10 of 2000, s. 104.`
  line
  line `6. Renumbered by Act 33 of 2009, s. 105(ii).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 105(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_aa:
  sectionId (72862)
  sectionNo 14AA
  orderNo 45
  title `Special audit in cases where credit of duty availed or utilised is not within the normal limits, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_aa_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_aa_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72862&sectionno=14AA&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_14_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[14AA. Special audit in cases where credit of duty availed or utilised is not within the normal`
  line `limits, etc.--(1) If the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise]`
  line
  line `has reason to believe that the credit of duty availed of or utilised under the rules made under this Act by a`
  line `manufacturer of any excisable goods--`
  line
  line `(a) is not within the normal limits having regard to the nature of the excisable goods produced or`
  line `manufactured, the type of inputs used and other relevant factors, as he may deem appropriate;`
  line
  line `(b) has been availed of or utilised by reason of fraud, collusion or any wilful misstatement or`
  line `suppression of facts,`
  line
  line `he may direct such manufacturer to get the accounts of his factory, office, depot, distributor or any other`
  line `place, as may be specified by him, audited by a ^3[cost accountant or chartered accountant] nominated by`
  line him.
  line
  line `(2) The ^3[cost accountant or chartered accountant so nominated shall, within the period specified by`
  line `the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise], submit a report of`
  line `such audit duly signed and certified by him to the said Commissioner mentioning therein such other`
  line `particulars as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall have effect notwithstanding that the accounts of the said`
  line `manufacturer aforesaid have been audited under any other law for the time being in force or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(4)`
  line `^4[* * *]`
  line
  line `(5) The manufacturer shall be given an opportunity of being heard in respect of any material gathered`
  line `on the basis of the audit under sub-section (1) and proposed to be utilised in any proceeding under this Act`
  line `or rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `^5[Explanation 1.]-- For the purpose of this section, "cost accountant" shall have the meaning assigned`
  line `to it in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of Section 2 of the Cost and Works Accountants Act, 1959 (23 of 1959).`
  line
  line `^6[Explanation 2.-- For the purposes of this section, "chartered accountant" shall have the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of Section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of`
  line `1949).]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_aa_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 83.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 106(i), for "cost accountant".`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by Act 10 of 2000, S. 105.`
  line
  line `5. Explanation renumbered by Act 33 of 2009, s. 106(i) & (ii).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 106(i) & (ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (71987)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 46
  title `Officers required to assist Central Excise Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71987&sectionno=15&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `All officers of Police and Customs and all`
  line `officers of Government engaged in the collection of land revenue, and all village officers are hereby`
  line `empowered and required to assist the Central Excise Officers in the execution of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (71988)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 47
  title `Obligation to furnish information return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 97.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71988&sectionno=15A&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Obligation to furnish information return.-- (1) Any person, being--`
  line
  line `(a) an assessee; or`
  line
  line `(b) a local authority or other public body or association; or`
  line
  line `(c) any authority of the State Government responsible for the collection of value added tax or`
  line `sales tax; or`
  line
  line `(d) an income tax authority appointed under the provisions of the Income Tax Act, 1961 (43 of`
  line `1961); or`
  line
  line `(e) a banking company within the meaning of clause (a) of Section 45-A of the Reserve Bank`
  line `of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934); or`
  line
  line `(f) a State Electricity Board or an electricity distribution or transmission licensee under the`
  line `Electricity Act, 2003 (36 of 2003), or any other entity entrusted, as the case may be, with such`
  line `functions by the Central Government or the State Government; or`
  line
  line `(g) the Registrar or Sub-Registrar appointed under Section 6 of the Registration Act, 1908 (16`
  line `of 1908); or`
  line
  line `(h) a Registrar within the meaning of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013); or`
  line
  line `(i) the registering authority empowered to register motor vehicles under Chapter IV of the`
  line `Motor Vehicles Act, 1988 (59 of 1988); or`
  line
  line `(j) the Collector referred to in clause (c) of Section 3 of the Right to Fair Compensation and`
  line `Transparency in Land Acquisition, Rehabilitation and Resettlement Act, 2013 (30 of 2013); or`
  line
  line `(k) the recognised stock exchange referred to in clause (f) of Section 2 of the Securities`
  line `Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956); or`
  line
  line `(l) a depository referred to in clause (e) of sub-section (1) of Section 2 of the Depositories Act,`
  line `1996 (22 of 1996); or`
  line
  line `(m) an officer of the Reserve Bank of India, constituted under Section 3 of the Reserve Bank`
  line `of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934),`
  line
  line `who is responsible for maintaining record of registration or statement of accounts or any periodic return`
  line `or document containing details of payment of tax and other details or transaction of goods or services or`
  line `transactions related to a bank account or consumption of electricity or transaction of purchase, sale or`
  line `exchange of goods or property or right or interest in a property, under any law for the time being in force,`
  line `shall furnish an information return of the same in respect of such periods, within such time, form (including`
  line `electronic form) and manner, to such authority or agency as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the prescribed authority considers that the information submitted in the information return`
  line `is defective, he may intimate the defect to the person who has furnished such information return and give`
  line `him an opportunity of rectifying the defect within a period of thirty days from the date of such intimation`
  line `or within such further period which, on an application made in this behalf, the prescribed authority may`
  line `allow and if the defect is not rectified within the said period of thirty days or, as the case may be, the further`
  line `period so allowed, then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, such`
  line `information return shall be treated as not submitted and the provisions of this Act shall apply.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person who is required to furnish information return has not furnished the same within the`
  line `time specified in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the prescribed authority may serve upon him a notice`
  line `requiring furnishing of such information return within a period not exceeding ninety days from the date of`
  line `service of the notice and such person shall furnish the information return.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_b:
  sectionId (71989)
  sectionNo 15B
  orderNo 48
  title `Penalty for failure to furnish information return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, S. 97.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71989&sectionno=15B&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[15B. Penalty for failure to furnish information return.-- If a person who is required to furnish an`
  line `information return under Section 15-A fails to do so within the period specified in the notice issued under`
  line `sub-section (3) thereof, the prescribed authority may direct that such person shall pay, by way of penalty, a`
  line `sum of one hundred rupees for each day of the period during which the failure to furnish such return`
  line continues.]
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (71990)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 49
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71990&sectionno=16&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
