  line `goods].--- Omitted by Finance Act 2002 (20 of 2002), s. 137.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (71991)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 50
  title [Omitted.].
  content `[Punishment for connivance at offences].--- Omitted by s. 137, ibid`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71991&sectionno=17&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (71992)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 51
  title `Searches and arrests how to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. See now the CrPC, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71992&sectionno=18&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `All searches made under this Act or any rules made`
  line `thereunder and all arrests made under this Act shall be carried out in accordance with the provisions of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)^2`
  line `, relating respectively to searches and arrests made under`
  line `that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (71993)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 52
  title `Disposal of persons arrested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71993&sectionno=19&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Every person arrested under this Act shall be forwarded without`
  line `delay to the nearest Central Excise Officer empowered to send persons so arrested to a Magistrate, or, if`
  line `there is no such Central Excise Officer within a reasonable distance, to the officer-in-charge of the nearest`
  line `police station.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (71994)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 53
  title `Procedure to be followed by officer-in-charge of police station.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71994&sectionno=20&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The officer-in-charge of a`
  line `police station to whom any person is forwarded under Section 19 1`
  line `shall, where the offence is noncognizable, either admit him to bail to appear before the Magistrate having jurisdiction, or in default of`
  line `bail forward him in custody to such Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (72863)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 54
  title `Inquiry how to be made by Central Excise Officers against arrested persons forwarded to them under Section 19.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72863&sectionno=21&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person is forwarded under Section 19 to a Central Excise Officer`
  line `empowered to send persons so arrested to a Magistrate, the Central Excise Officer shall proceed to inquire`
  line `into the charge against him.`
  line
  line `(2) For this purpose the Central Excise Officer may exercise the same powers and shall be subject to`
  line `the same provisions as the officer-in-charge of a police station may exercise and is subject to under the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)^1`
  line `, when investigating a cognizable case:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) if the Central Excise Officer is of opinion that there is sufficient evidence or reasonable ground`
  line `of suspicion against the accused person, he ^3[shall, where the offence is non-cognizable, either admit`
  line `him] to bail to appear before a Magistrate having jurisdiction in the case, or forward him in custody to`
  line `such Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(b) if it appears to the Central Excise Officer that there is not sufficient evidence or reasonable`
  line `ground of suspicion against the accused person ^3[in respect of offence which is non-cognizable], he`
  line `shall release the accused person on his executing a bond, with or without sureties as the Central Excise`
  line `Officer may direct, to appear, if and when so required, before the Magistrate having jurisdiction, and`
  line `shall make a full report of all the particulars of the case to his official superior.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 93, for "shall either admit him".`
  line
  line `2. See now the CrPC, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 94(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (71996)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 55
  title `Vexatious search, seizure, etc., by Central Excise Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71996&sectionno=22&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Any Central Excise or other officer`
  line `exercising powers under this Act or under the rules made thereunder who--`
  line
  line `(a) without reasonable ground of suspicion searches or causes to be searched any house, boat or`
  line place;
  line
  line `(b) vexatiously and unnecessarily detains, searches or arrests any person;`
  line
  line `(c) vexatiously and unnecessarily seizes the movable property of any person, on pretence of seizing`
  line `or searching for any article liable to confiscation under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) commits, as such officer, any other act to the injury of any person, without having reason to`
  line `believe that such act is required for the execution of his duty;`
  line
  line `shall, for every such offence, be punishable with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `Any person wilfully and maliciously giving false information and so causing an arrest or a search to be`
  line `made under this Act shall be punishable with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees or with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (71997)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 56
  title `Failure of Central Excise Officer in duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71997&sectionno=23&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Any Central Excise Officer who ceases or refuses to`
  line `perform or withdraws himself from the duties of his office, unless he has obtained the express written`
  line `permission of the ^1[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise], or has`
  line `given to his superior officer two months' notice in writing of his intention or has other lawful excuse, shall`
  line `on conviction before a Magistrate be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `months, or with fine which may extend to three months' pay, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_a:
  sectionId (71998)
  sectionNo 23A
  orderNo 57
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71998&sectionno=23A&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[23A. Definitions.--In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) "activity" means production or manufacture of goods and includes any new business of`
  line `production or manufacture proposed to be undertaken by the existing producer or manufacturer, as the`
  line `case may be;]`
  line
  line `(b) "advance ruling" means the determination, by the authority of a question of law or fact specified`
  line `in the application regarding the liability to pay duty in relation to an activity proposed to be undertaken,`
  line `by the applicant;`
  line
  line `^3[(c) "applicant" means--`
  line
  line `(i) (a) a non-resident setting up a joint venture in India in collaboration with a non-resident or a`
  line `resident; or`
  line
  line `(b) a resident setting up a joint venture in India in collaboration with a non-resident; or`
  line
  line `(c) a wholly owned subsidiary Indian company, of which the holding company is a foreign`
  line company,
  line
  line `who or which, as the case may be, proposes to undertake any business activity in India;`
  line
  line `(ii) a joint venture in India; or`
  line
  line `(iii) a resident falling within any such class or category of persons, as the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf,`
  line
  line `and which or who, as the case may be, makes application for advance ruling under sub-section (1)`
  line `of Section 23-C;]`
  line
  line `^4[Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, "joint venture in India" means a contractual`
  line `arrangement whereby two or more persons undertake an economic activity which is subject to joint`
  line `control and one or more of the participants or partners or equity holders is a non-resident having`
  line `substantial interest in such arrangement;]`
  line
  line `(d) "application" means an application made to the Authority under sub-section (1) of`
  line `Section 23-C;`
  line
  line `^5[(e) "Authority" means the Authority for Advance Rulings as defined in clause (e) of`
  line `Section 28-E of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962);]`
  line
  line `^6[(f) "non-resident", "Indian company" and "foreign company" shall have the meaning assigned to`
  line `them in clauses (30), (26) and (23-A) of Section 2 of the Income Tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961).]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. New Chapter III-A consisting of Ss. 23-A to 23-H ins. by Act 27 of 1999, S. 124.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 95 for clause (a) "activity" means production or manufacture of goods;.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 76, for clause (c).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 118.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 112 for clause (e).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 142, for clause (f).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_b:
  sectionId (71999)
  sectionNo 23B
  orderNo 58
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_b_content
  footnotes `1. New Chapter III-A consisting of Ss. 23-A to 23-H ins. by Act 27 of 1999, S. 124.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=71999&sectionno=23B&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_23_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[23B.[Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings].-- Omitted by Finance Act 2017 (7 of 2017), s.`
  line 113.]
obj_root_law_sections_23_c:
  sectionId (72001)
  sectionNo 23C
  orderNo 59
  title `Application for advance ruling.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72001&sectionno=23C&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_23_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[23C. Application for advance ruling.-- (1) An applicant desirous of obtaining an advance ruling`
  line `under this Chapter may make an application in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed, stating`
  line `the question on which the advance ruling is sought.`
  line
  line `(2) The question on which the advance ruling is sought shall be in respect of,--`
  line
  line `(a) classification of any goods under the Central Excise Tariff Act, 1985;`
  line
  line `(b) applicability of a notification issued under sub-section (1) of Section 5A having a bearing on`
  line `the rate of duty;`
  line
  line `(c) the principles to be adopted for the purposes of determination of value of the goods under the`
  line `provisions of this Act;]`
  line
  line `^2[(d) notifications issued, in respect of duties of excise under this Act, the Central Excise Tariff`
  line `Act, 1985 (5 of 1986) and any duty chargeable under any other law for the time being in force in the`
  line `same manner as duty of excise leviable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e)`
  line `^3[admissibility of credit of service tax paid or deemed to have been paid on input service or`
  line `excise duty] paid or deemed to have been paid on the goods used in or in relation to the manufacture of`
  line `the excisable goods;]`
  line
  line `^4[(f) determination of the liability to pay duties of excise on any goods under this Act.]`
  line
  line `(3) The application shall be made in quadruplicate and be accompanied by a fee of ^5[ten thousand`
  line rupees].
  line
  line `(4) An applicant may withdraw an application within thirty days from the date of the application.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. New Chapter III-A consisting of Ss. 23-A to 23-H ins. by Act 27 of 1999, S. 124.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 143.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 96, for "admissibility of credit of excise duty".`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 65.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 114, for "two thousand five hundred rupees".`
obj_root_law_sections_23_d:
  sectionId (72002)
  sectionNo 23D
  orderNo 60
  title `Procedure on receipt of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72002&sectionno=23D&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_23_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[23D. Procedure on receipt of application.--- (1) On receipt of an application, the Authority shall cause`
  line `a copy thereof to be forwarded to the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of`
  line `Central Excise] and, if necessary, call upon him to furnish the relevant records:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any records have been called for by the Authority in any case, such records`
  line `shall, as soon as possible, be returned to the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise].`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority may, after examining the application and the records called for, by order, either allow`
  line `or reject the application:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority shall not allow the application ^3[* * *] where the question raised in the`
  line `application is,--`
  line
  line `(a) already pending in the applicants case before any Central Excise Officer, the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal or any Court;`
  line
  line `(b) the same as in a matter already decided by the Appellate Tribunal or any Court:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no application shall be rejected under this sub-section unless an`
  line `opportunity has been given to the applicant of being heard:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where the application is rejected, reasons for such rejection shall be given in`
  line `the order.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of every order made under sub-section (2) shall be sent to the applicant and to the ^4[Principal`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise].`
  line
  line `(4) Where an application is allowed under sub-section (2), the Authority shall, after examining such`
  line `further material as may be placed before it by the applicant or obtained by the Authority, pronounce its`
  line `advance ruling on the question specified in the application.`
  line
  line `(5) On a request received from the applicant, the Authority shall, before pronouncing its advance ruling,`
  line `provide an opportunity to the applicant of being heard, either in person or through a duly authorised`
  line representative.
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, "authorised representative" shall have the`
  line `meaning assigned to it in sub-section (2) of Section 35-Q.`
  line
  line `(6) The Authority shall pronounce its advance ruling in writing within ^5[six months] of the receipt of`
  line application.
  line
  line `(7) A copy of the advance ruling pronounced by the Authority, duly signed by the Members and`
  line `certified in the prescribed manner shall be sent to the applicant and to the ^4[Principal Commissioner of`
  line `Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise], as soon as may be, after such pronouncement.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. New Chapter III-A consisting of Ss. 23-A to 23-H ins. by Act 27 of 1999, S. 124.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `3. The words "except in the case of a resident applicant" omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 138.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 115, for "ninety days".`
obj_root_law_sections_23_e:
  sectionId (72003)
  sectionNo 23E
  orderNo 61
  title `Applicability of advance ruling.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72003&sectionno=23E&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_23_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[23E. Applicability of advance ruling.-- (1) The advance ruling pronounced by the Authority under`
  line `Section 23D shall be binding only--`
  line
  line `(a) on the applicant who had sought it;`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of any matter referred to in sub-section (2) of Section 23C;`
  line
  line `(c) on the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise", and the`
  line `Central Excise Authorities subordinate to him, in request of the applicant.`
  line
  line `(2) The advance ruling referred to in sub-section (1) shall be binding as aforesaid unless there is a`
  line `change in law or facts on the basis of which the advance ruling has been pronounced.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. New Chapter III-A consisting of Ss. 23-A to 23-H ins. by Act 27 of 1999, S. 124.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
obj_root_law_sections_23_f:
  sectionId (72004)
  sectionNo 23F
  orderNo 62
  title `Advance ruling to be void in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_f_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_f_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72004&sectionno=23F&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_23_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[23F. Advance ruling to be void in certain circumstances.--(1) Where the Authority finds, on a`
  line `representation made to it by the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central`
  line `Excise] or otherwise, that an advance ruling pronounced by it under sub-section (6) of ^3[Section 23D] has`
  line `been obtained by the applicant by fraud or misrepresentation of facts, it may, by order, declare such ruling`
  line `to be void ab initio and thereupon all the provisions of this Act shall apply (after excluding the period beginning with the date of such advance ruling and ending with the date of order under this sub-section) to`
  line `the applicant as if such advance ruling had never been made.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the order made under sub-section (1) shall be sent to the applicant and the ^4[Principal`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise].`
obj_root_law_sections_23_f_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 143.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 97, for "Section 28I".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
obj_root_law_sections_23_g:
  sectionId (72005)
  sectionNo 23G
  orderNo 63
  title `Powers of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_g_content
  footnotes `1. New Chapter III-A consisting of Ss. 23-A to 23-H ins. by Act 27 of 1999, S. 124.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72005&sectionno=23G&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_23_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[23G. Powers of Authority.--(1) The Authority shall, for the purpose of exercising its powers`
  line `regarding discovery and inspection, enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath,`
  line `issuing commissions and compelling production of books of account and other records, have all the powers`
  line `of a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of Section 195, but not for the`
  line `purposes of Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 and every proceeding before the`
  line `Authority shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of Sections 193 and 228, and for`
  line `the purpose of Section 196 of the Indian Penal Code.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_h:
  sectionId (72006)
  sectionNo 23H
  orderNo 64
  title `Procedure of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_h_content
  footnotes `1. New Chapter III-A consisting of Ss. 23-A to 23-H ins. by Act 27 of 1999, S. 124.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72006&sectionno=23H&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_23_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[23H. Procedure of Authority.--The Authority shall, subject to the provisions of this Chapter, have`
  line `power to regulate its own procedure in all matters arising out of the exercise of its powers under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_i:
  sectionId (72007)
