obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (72015)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 73
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72015&sectionno=31&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1[31. Definitions.--In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires.--`
  line
  line `(a) "assessee" means any person who is liable for payment of excise duty assessed under this Act`
  line `or any other Act and includes any producer or manufacturer of excisable goods or a registered person`
  line `under the rules made under this Act, of a private warehouse in which excisable goods are stored;`
  line
  line `(b) "Bench" means a Bench of the Settlement Commission;`
  line
  line `^2[(c) "case" means any proceeding under this Act or any other Act for the levy, assessment and`
  line `collection of excise duty, pending before an adjudicating authority on the date on which an application`
  line `under sub-section (1) of Section 32-E is made:`
  line
  line `Provided that when any proceeding is referred back ^3[* * *] by any court, Appellate Tribunal or`
  line `any other authority, to the adjudicating authority for a fresh adjudication or decision, as the case may`
  line `be, then such proceeding shall not be deemed to be a proceeding pending within the meaning of this`
  line clause,]
  line
  line `(d) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the Settlement Commission;`
  line
  line `(e) "Commissioner (Investigation)" means an officer of the Customs or a Central Excise Officer`
  line `appointed as such Commissioner to conduct inquiry or investigation for the purposes of this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(f) "Member" means a Member of the Settlement Commission and includes the Chairman and the`
  line Vice-Chairman;
  line
  line `(g) "Settlement Commission" means the ^4[Customs, Central Excise and Service Tax Settlement`
  line `Commission] constituted under Section 32; and`
  line
  line `(h) "Vice-Chairman" means a Vice-Chairman of the Settlement Commission.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by ibid. s. 110.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 119, for clause (c), (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line
  line `3. The words "in any appeal or revision, as the case may be," omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 95.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 98, for "Customs and Central Excise Settlement Commission".`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (72016)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 74
  title `Customs and Central Excise Settlement Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72016&sectionno=32&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `^1[32. Customs and Central Excise Settlement Commission.--(1) The Central Government shall, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, constitute a Commission to be called ^2[the Customs, Central Excise and`
  line `Service Tax Settlement Commission] for the settlement of cases under this Chapter and Chapter XIV-A of`
  line `the Customs Act, 1962.`
  line
  line `(2) The Settlement Commission shall consist of a Chairman and as many Vice-Chairmen and other`
  line `Members as the Central Government thinks fit and shall function within the Department of the Central`
  line `Government dealing with Customs and Central Excise matters.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman, Vice-Chairman and other Members of the Settlement Commission shall be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government from amongst persons of integrity and outstanding ability, having`
  line `special knowledge of, and experience in, administration of customs and central excise laws:]`
  line
  line `^3[* * *]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 99, for "the Customs and Central Excise Settlement Commission".`
  line
  line `3. Proviso omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 96.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_a:
  sectionId (72017)
  sectionNo 32A
  orderNo 75
  title `Jurisdiction and powers of Settlement Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72017&sectionno=32A&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content:
  string
  line `^2[32A. Jurisdiction and powers of Settlement Commission.-- (1) Subject to the other provisions of`
  line `this Chapter, the jurisdiction, powers and authority of the Settlement Commission may be exercised by`
  line `Benches thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the other provisions of this section, a Bench shall be presided over by the Chairman or a`
  line `Vice-Chairman and shall consist of two other Members.`
  line
  line `(3) The Bench for which the Chairman is the presiding officer shall be the principal Bench and other`
  line `Benches shall be known as additional Benches.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) and sub-section (2), the Chairman may`
  line `authorise the Vice-Chairman or other Member appointed to one Bench to discharge also the functions of`
  line `the Vice-Chairman or, as the case may be, other Member of another Bench.`
  line
  line `(5) The principal Bench shall sit at Delhi and the Central Government shall, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, establish additional Benches at such places as it considers necessary.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, and subject to any`
  line `rules that may be made in this behalf, when one of the persons constituting a Bench (whether such person`
  line `be the presiding officer or other Member of the Bench) is unable to discharge his functions owing to`
  line `absence, illness or any other cause or in the event of the occurrence of any vacancy either in the office of`
  line `the presiding officer or in the office of one or the other Members of the Bench, the remaining Members`
  line `may function as the Bench and if the presiding officer of the Bench is not one of the remaining Members,`
  line `the senior among the remaining Members shall act as the presiding officer of the Bench:`
  line
  line `Provided that if at any stage of the hearing of any such case or matter, it appears to the presiding`
  line `officer that the case or matter is of such a nature that it ought to be heard of by a Bench consisting of`
  line `three Members, the case or matter may be referred by the presiding officer of such Bench to the`
  line `Chairman for transfer to such Bench as the Chairman may deem fit:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided further that at any stage of the hearing of any such case or matter, referred to in the first`
  line `proviso, the Chairman may, if he thinks that the case or matter is of such a nature that it ought to be heard`
  line `by a Bench consisting of three Members, constitute such Bench and if Vice-Chairman is not one of the`
  line `Members, the senior among the Members shall act as the presiding officer of such Bench.]`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, the Chairman may,`
  line `for the disposal of any particular case, constitute a special Bench consisting of more than three Members.`
  line
  line `(8) Subject to the other provisions of this Chapter, the special Bench shall sit at a place to be fixed by`
  line `the Chairman.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 120.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_b:
  sectionId (72018)
  sectionNo 32B
  orderNo 76
  title `Vice-Chairman to act as Chairman or to discharge his functions in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72018&sectionno=32B&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[32B. Vice-Chairman to act as Chairman or to discharge his functions in certain`
  line `circumstances.--(1) In the event of the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Chairman by reason`
  line `of his death, resignation or otherwise, the Vice-Chairman or ^2[the Member] as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, authorise in this behalf, shall act as the Chairman until the date`
  line `on which a new Chairman, appointed in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter to fill such vacancy,`
  line `enters upon his office.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Chairman is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence, illness or any other cause,`
  line `the Vice-Chairman or ^2[the Member] as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, authorise in this behalf, shall discharge the functions of the Chairman until the date on which the`
  line `Chairman resumes his duties.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 97, for ", as the case may be, such one of the Vice-Chairmen".`
obj_root_law_sections_32_c:
  sectionId (72019)
  sectionNo 32C
  orderNo 77
  title `Power of Chairman to transfer cases from one Bench to another.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72019&sectionno=32C&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[32C. Power of Chairman to transfer cases from one Bench to another.---On the application of`
  line `the assessee or the Chief Commissioner or ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner`
  line `of Central Excise] and after giving notice to them, and after hearing such of them as he may desire to be`
  line `heard, or on his own motion without such notice, the Chairman may transfer any case pending before one`
  line `Bench, for disposal, to another Bench.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
obj_root_law_sections_32_d:
  sectionId (72020)
  sectionNo 32D
  orderNo 78
  title `Decision to be by majority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72020&sectionno=32D&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[32D. Decision to be by majority.---If the Members of a Bench differ in opinion on any point, the`
  line `point shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority, if there is a majority, but if the Members`
  line `are equally divided, they shall state the point or points on which they differ, and make a reference to the`
  line `Chairman who shall either hear the point or points himself or refer the case for hearing on such point or`
  line `points by one or more of the other Members of the Settlement Commission and such point or points shall`
  line `be decided according to the opinion of the majority of the Members of the Settlement Commission who`
  line `have heard the case, including those who first heard it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_e:
  sectionId (72021)
  sectionNo 32E
  orderNo 79
  title `Application for settlement of cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72021&sectionno=32E&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[32E. Application for settlement of cases.-- ^2](1) An assessee may, in respect of a case relating to`
  line `him, make an application, before adjudication, to the Settlement Commission to have the case settled, in`
  line `such form and in such manner as may be prescribed and containing a full and true disclosure of his duty`
  line `liability which has not been disclosed before the Central Excise Officer having jurisdiction, the manner in`
  line `which such liability has been derived, the additional amount of excise duty accepted to be payable by him`
  line `and such other particulars as may be prescribed including the particulars of such excisable goods in respect`
  line `of which he admits short levy on account of misclassification, under-valuation, inapplicability of exemption`
  line `notification or CENVAT credit ^3[or otherwise] and any such application shall be disposed of in the manner`
  line `hereinafter provided:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such application shall be made unless,---`
  line
  line `(a) the applicant has filed returns showing production, clearance and central excise duty paid in the`
  line `prescribed manner;`
  line
  line `(b) a show cause notice for recovery of duty issued by the Central Excise Officer has been received`
  line `by the applicant;`
  line
  line `(c) the additional amount of duty accepted by the applicant in his application exceeds three lakh`
  line `rupees; and`
  line
  line `(d) the applicant has paid the additional amount of excise duty accepted by him along with interest`
  line `due under ^4[Section 11AA]:br`
  line
  line `^5[Provided further that the Settlement Commission, if it is satisfied that the circumstances exist for not`
  line `filing the returns referred to in clause (a) of the first proviso to sub-section (1), may after recording the`
  line `reasons therefor, allow the applicant to make such application:br`
  line
  line `Provided also that] no application shall be entertained by the Settlement Commission under this`
  line `sub-section in cases which are pending with the Appellate Tribunal or any court:`
  line `Provided also that no application under this sub-section shall be made for the interpretation of the`
  line `classification of excisable goods under the Central Excise Tariff Act, 1985 (5 of 1986).`
  line `(1A) ^6[* * *]]br`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line `^7[* * *]br`
  line
  line `(3) Every application made under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by such fees as may be`
  line prescribed.br
  line
  line `(4) An application made under sub-section (1) shall not be allowed to be withdrawn by the applicant.`
  line `^8[(5) Any person other than an assessee, may also make an application to the Settlement Commission`
  line `in respect of a show-cause notice issued to him in a case relating to the assessee which has been settled or`
  line `is pending before the Settlement Commission and such notice is pending before an adjudicating authority,`
  line `in such manner and subject to such conditions, as may be prescribed.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 121, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 65, for “but excluding the goods in respect of which no proper record has been maintained by the`
  line `assessee in his daily stock register".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 100(i)(a), for "Section 11AB".`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by ibid., s. 100(i)(b), for “Provided further that".`
  line
  line `6. Sub-section (1A) omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 98.`
  line
  line `7. Omitted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 100(ii).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 117.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_f:
  sectionId (72022)
  sectionNo 32F
  orderNo 80
  title `Procedure on receipt of an application under Section 32-E.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_f_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_f_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72022&sectionno=32F&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_f_content:
  string
  line `^2[^3[32F. Procedure on receipt of an application under Section 32E.--(1) On receipt of an`
  line `application under ^3[* * *] Section 32E, the Settlement Commission shall, within seven days from the date`
  line `of receipt of the application, issue a notice to the applicant to explain in writing as to why the application`
  line `made by him should be allowed to be proceeded with, and after taking into consideration the explanation`
  line `provided by the applicant, the Settlement Commission, shall, within a period of fourteen days from the date`
  line `of the notice, by an order, allow the application to be proceeded with, or reject the application as the case`
  line `may be, and the proceedings before the Settlement Commission shall abate on the date of rejection:`
  line
  line `Provided that where no notice has been issued or no order has been passed within the aforesaid period`
  line `by the Settlement Commission, the application shall be deemed to have been allowed to be proceeded with.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every order under sub-section (1), shall be sent to the applicant and to the ^4`
  line [Principal
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] having jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an application is allowed or deemed to have been allowed to be proceeded with under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Settlement Commission shall, within seven days from the date of order under`
  line `sub-section (1), call for a report along with the relevant records from the ^4[Principal Commissioner of`
  line `Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] having jurisdiction and the Commissioner shall furnish`
  line `the report within a period of thirty days of the receipt of communication from the Settlement Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Commissioner does not furnish the report within the aforesaid period of`
  line `thirty days, the Settlement Commission shall proceed further in the matter without the report of the`
  line Commissioner.
  line
  line `(4) Where a report of the Commissioner called for under sub-section (3) has been furnished within the`
  line `period specified in that sub-section, the Settlement Commission may, after examination of such report, if it`
  line `is of the opinion that any further enquiry or investigation in the matter is necessary, direct, for reasons to be recorded in writing, the Commissioner (Investigation) within fifteen days of the receipt of the report, to`
  line `make or cause to be made such further enquiry or investigation and furnish a report within a period of ninety`
  line `days of the receipt of the communication from the Settlement Commission, on the matters covered by the`
  line `application and any other matter relating to the case:]`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Commissioner (Investigation) does not furnish the report within the`
  line `aforesaid period, the Settlement Commission shall proceed to pass an order under sub-section (5)`
  line `without such report.`
  line
  line `(5) After examination of the records and the report of the ^4[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise`
  line `or Commissioner of Central Excise] received under sub-section (3), and the report, if any, of the`
  line `Commissioner (Investigation) of the Settlement Commission under sub-section (4), and after giving an`
  line `opportunity to the applicant and to the ^4[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of`
  line `Central Excise] having jurisdiction to be heard, either in person or through a representative duly authorised`
  line `in this behalf, and after examining such further evidence as may be placed before it or obtained by it, the`
  line `Settlement Commission may, in accordance with the provisions of this Act, pass such order as it thinks fit`
  line `on the matters covered by the application and any other matter relating to the case not covered by the`
  line `application, but referred to in the report of the ^4[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner`
  line `of Central Excise] and Commissioner (Investigation) under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `^5[(5A) The Settlement Commission may, at any time within three months from the date of passing of`
  line `the order under sub-section (5), amend such order to rectify any error apparent on the face of record, either`
  line `suo motu or when such error is brought to its notice by the jurisdictional Principal Commissioner of Central`
  line `Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise or the applicant:`
  line
  line `Provided that no amendment which has the effect of enhancing the liability of the applicant shall`
  line `be made under this sub-section, unless the Settlement Commission has given notice of such intention`
  line `to the applicant and the jurisdictional Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of`
  line `Central Excise as the case may be, and has given them a reasonable opportunity of being heard.]`
  line
  line `(6) An order under sub-section (5) shall not be passed in respect of an application filed ^6[* * *] after`
  line `nine months from the last day of the month in which the application was made, failing which the settlement`
  line `proceedings shall abate, and the adjudicating authority before whom the proceeding at the time of making`
  line `the application was pending, shall dispose of the case in accordance with the provisions of this Act as if no`
  line `application under Section 32-E had been made:`
  line
  line `^7[Provided that the period specified under this sub-section may, for reasons to be recorded in writing,`
  line `be extended by the Settlement Commission for a further period not exceeding three months.]`
  line
  line `(7) Subject to the provisions of Section 32A, the materials brought on record before the Settlement`
  line `Commission shall be considered by the Members of the concerned Bench before passing any order under`
  line `sub-section (5) and, in relation to the passing of such order, the provisions of Section 32D shall apply.`
  line
  line `(8) The order passed under sub-section (5) shall provide for the terms of settlement including any`
  line `demand by way of duty, penalty or interest, the manner in which any sums due under the settlement shall`
  line `be paid and all other matters to make the settlement effective and in case of rejection contain the reasons`
  line `therefor and it shall also provide that the settlement shall be void if it is subsequently found by the`
  line `Settlement Commission that it has been obtained by fraud or misrepresentation of facts:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of settlement ordered by the Settlement Commission shall not be less`
  line `than the duty liability admitted by the applicant under Section 32E.`
  line
  line `(9) Where any duty, interest, fine and penalty payable in pursuance of an order under sub-section (5),`
  line `is not paid by the assessee within thirty days of receipt of a copy of the order by him, the amount which`
  line `remains unpaid, shall be recovered along with interest due thereon, as the sums due to the Central`
  line `Government by the Central Excise Officer having jurisdiction over the assessee in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of Section 11.`
  line
  line `(10) Where a settlement becomes void as provided under sub-section (8), the proceedings with respect`
  line `to the matters covered by the settlement shall be deemed to have been revived from the stage at which the`
  line `application was allowed to be proceeded with by the Settlement Commission and the Central Excise Officer`
  line `having jurisdiction may, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, complete`
  line `such proceedings at any time before the expiry of two years from the date of the receipt of communication`
  line `that the settlement became void.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_f_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 122, for "section 32F" (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line
  line `3. The word "sub-section (1) of" omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 118(i).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 118(ii).`
  line
  line `6. The words "on or before the 31st day of May, 2007, later than the 29th day of February, 2008 and in respect of an application`
  line `made on or after the 1st day of June, 2007," omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 99.`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 66.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_g:
  sectionId (72023)
  sectionNo 32G
  orderNo 81
  title `Power of Settlement Commission to order provisional attachment to protect revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72023&sectionno=32G&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[32G. Power of Settlement Commission to order provisional attachment to protect revenue.--`
  line `Where, during the pendency of any proceeding before it, the Settlement Commission is of the opinion that`
  line `for the purpose of protecting the interests of revenue it is necessary so to do, it may, by order, attach`
  line `provisionally any property belonging to the applicant in the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every provisional attachment made by the Settlement Commission under sub-section (1) shall cease`
  line `to have effect from the date, the sums due to the Central Government for which such attachment is made`
  line `are discharged by the applicant and evidence to that effect is submitted to the Settlement Commission.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_h:
  sectionId (72024)
  sectionNo 32H
  orderNo 82
  title `Power of Settlement Commission to reopen completed proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_h_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72024&sectionno=32H&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[32H. ]Power of Settlement Commission to reopen completed proceedings.--Omitted by Finance`
  line `Act 2015 (Act 20 of 2015), s. 100. ]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_i:
  sectionId (72025)
  sectionNo 32I
  orderNo 83
  title `Powers and procedure of Settlement Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_i_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_i_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72025&sectionno=32I&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[32I. Powers and procedure of Settlement Commission.--(1) In addition to the powers conferred`
  line `on the Settlement Commission under this Chapter, it shall have all the powers which are vested in a Central`
  line `Excise Officer under this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an application made under Section 32E has been allowed to be proceeded with under Section`
  line `32F, the Settlement Commission shall, until an order is passed under sub-section ^2[(5)] of Section 32F,`
  line `have, subject to the provisions of sub-section ^3[(4)] of that section, exclusive jurisdiction to exercise the`
  line `powers and perform the functions of any Central Excise Officer, under this Act in relation to the case.`
  line
  line `(3) In the absence of any express direction by the Settlement Commission to the contrary, nothing in`
  line `this Chapter shall affect the operation of the provisions of this Act in so far as they relate to any matters`
  line `other upon those before the Settlement Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The Settlement Commission shall, subject to the provisions of this Chapter, have power to regulate`
  line `its own procedure and the procedure of Benches thereof in all matters arising out of the exercise of its`
  line `powers, or of the discharge of its functions, including the places at which the Benches shall hold their`
  line sittings.]
obj_root_law_sections_32_i_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 124 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007), for "(7)".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by ibid, s. 124 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007), for "(6)".`
obj_root_law_sections_32_j:
  sectionId (72026)
  sectionNo 32J
  orderNo 84
  title `Inspection, etc., of reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_j_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72026&sectionno=32J&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_j_content:
  string
  line `^1[32J. Inspection, etc., of reports.--No person shall be entitled to inspect, or obtain copies of, any`
  line `report made by any Central Excise Officer to the Settlement Commission; but the Settlement Commission`
  line `may, in its discretion furnish copies thereof to any such person on an application made to it in this behalf`
  line `and on payment of the prescribed fee:`
  line
  line `Provided that, for the purpose of enabling any person whose case is under consideration to rebut any`
  line `evidence brought on record against him in any such report, the Settlement Commission shall, on an`
  line `application made in this behalf, and on payment of the prescribed fee by such person, furnish him with a`
  line `certified copy of any such report or part thereof relevant for the purpose.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_k:
  sectionId (72027)
  sectionNo 32K
  orderNo 85
  title `Power of Settlement Commission to grant immunity from prosecution and penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_k_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_k_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72027&sectionno=32K&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_k_content:
  string
  line `^1[32K. Power of Settlement Commission to grant immunity from prosecution and penalty.--The`
  line `Settlement Commission may, if it is satisfied that any person who made the application for settlement under`
  line `Section 32E has cooperated with the Settlement Commission in the proceedings before it and has made a`
  line `full and true disclosure of his duty liability, grant to such person, subject to such conditions as it may think`
  line `fit to impose, immunity from prosecution for any offence under this Act ^2[and also either wholly or in part from the imposition of any penalty and fine under this Act, with respect to the case covered by the`
  line `settlement:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such immunity shall be granted by the Settlement Commission in cases where the`
  line `proceedings for the prosecution for any such offence have been instituted before the date of receipt of the`
  line `application under Section 32E.`
  line
  line `^3[* * *]`
  line
  line `(2) An immunity granted to a person under sub-section (1) shall stand withdrawn if such person fails`
  line `to pay any sum specified in the order of the settlement passed under ^4[sub-section (5) of Section 32-F within`
  line `the time specified in such order], or fails to comply with any other condition subject to which the immunity`
  line `was granted and thereupon the provisions of this Act shall apply as if such immunity had not been granted.`
  line
  line `(3) An immunity granted to a person under sub-section (1) may, at any time, be withdrawn by the`
  line `Settlement Commission, if it is satisfied that such person had, in the course of the settlement proceedings,`
  line `concealed any particular material to the settlement or had given false evidence, and thereupon such person`
  line `may be tried for the offence with respect to which the immunity was granted or for any other offence of`
  line `which he appears to have been guilty in connection with the settlement and shall also become liable to the`
  line `imposition of any penalty under this Act to which such person would have been liable, had no such`
  line `immunity been granted.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_k_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by ibid, s. 125, for "or under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or under any other Central Act for the time being in`
  line `force and also either wholly or in part from the imposition of any penalty, fine and interest" (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Explanation omitted by Act 20 of 2015, S. 101.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 125, for "sub-section (7) of section 32F within the time specified in such order or within such`
  line `further time as may be allowed by the Settlement Commission" (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_l:
  sectionId (72028)
  sectionNo 32L
  orderNo 86
  title `Power of Settlement Commission to send a case back to the Central Excise Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_l_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72028&sectionno=32L&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_l_content:
  string
  line `^1[32L. Power of Settlement Commission to send a case back to the Central Excise Officer.--(1)`
  line `The Settlement Commission may, if it is of opinion that any person who made an application for settlement`
  line `under Section 32E has not cooperated with the Settlement Commission in the proceedings before it, send`
  line `the case back to the Central Excise Officer having jurisdiction who shall thereupon dispose of the case in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act as if no application under Section 32E had been made.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of sub-section (1), the Central Excise Officer shall be entitled to use all the materials`
  line `and other information produced by the assessee before the Settlement Commission or the results of the`
  line `inquiry held or evidence recorded by the Settlement Commission in the course of the proceedings before it`
  line `as if such materials, information, inquiry and evidence had been produced before such Central Excise`
  line `Officer or held or recorded by him in the course of the proceedings before him.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of the time-limit under Section 11A and for the purposes of interest under`
  line `Section 11BB, in a case referred to in sub-section (1), the period commencing on and from the date of the`
  line `application to the Settlement Commission under Section 32E and ending with the date of receipt by the Central Excise Officer of the order of the Settlement Commission sending the case back to the Central`
  line `Excise Officer shall be excluded.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_m:
  sectionId (72029)
  sectionNo 32M
  orderNo 87
  title `Order of settlement to be conclusive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_m_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_m_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72029&sectionno=32M&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_m_content:
  string
  line `^1[32M. Order of settlement to be conclusive.--Every order of settlement passed under`
  line `sub-section ^2[(5)] of Section 32-F shall be conclusive as to the matters stated therein and no matter covered`
  line `by such order shall, save as otherwise provided in this Chapter, be reopened in any proceeding under this`
  line `Act or under any other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_m_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 126, for "(7)" (w.e.f. 1-6-2007),.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_n:
  sectionId (72030)
  sectionNo 32N
  orderNo 88
  title `Recovery of sums due under order of settlement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_n_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_n_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72030&sectionno=32N&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_n_content:
  string
  line `^1[32N. Recovery of sums due under order of settlement.--Any sum specified in an order of`
  line `settlement passed under sub-section ^2[(5)] of Section 32-F may, subject to such conditions if any, as may`
  line `be specified therein, be recovered, and any penalty for default in making payment of such sum may be`
  line `imposed and recovered as sums due to the Central Government in accordance with the provisions under`
  line `Section 11 by the Central Excise Officer having jurisdiction over the person who made the application for`
  line `settlement under Section 32E.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_n_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 126, for "(7)" (w.e.f. 1-6-2007),.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_o:
  sectionId (72864)
  sectionNo 32O
  orderNo 89
  title `Bar on subsequent application for settlement in certain cases`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_o_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_o_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72864&sectionno=32O&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_o_content:
  string
  line `^1[32O. Bar on subsequent application for settlement in certain cases.-- ^2[(1)] ^3[Where, ^4[* * *]]--`
  line
  line `(i) an order of settlement ^5[* * *] provides for the imposition of a penalty on the person who made`
  line `the application under Section 32E for settlement, on the ground of concealment of particulars of his`
  line `duty liability; or`
  line
  line `^6[Explanation.--In this clause, the concealment of particulars of duty liability relates to any such`
  line `concealment made from the Central Excise Officer.]`
  line
  line `(ii) after the passing of an order of settlement ^7[* * *] in relation to a case, such person is convicted`
  line `of any offence under this Act in relation to that case; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the case of such person is sent back to the Central Excise Officer having jurisdiction by the`
  line `Settlement Commission under Section 32-L,`
  line
  line `then, he shall not be entitled to apply for settlement under Section 32-E in relation to any other`
  line matter.
  line
  line `(2)`
  line `^8[* * *]]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_o_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Renumbered by ibid, s. 128.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by ibid, s. 128, for "Where".`
  line
  line `4. The words "before the 1st day of June, 2007" Omitted by Act 14 of 2010, S. 67(a)(i).`
  line
  line `5. The words "passed under sub-section (7) of Section 32-F, as it stood immediately before the commencement of Section 122 of`
  line `the Finance Act, 2007 (22 of 2007) or sub-section (5) of Section 32-F" omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 102(a).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 101.`
  line
  line `7. The words "under the said sub-section (7), as it stood immediately before the commencement of Section 122 of the Finance`
  line `Act, 2007 (22 of 2007) or sub-section (5) of Section 32-F" omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 102(b).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 128 and omitted by Act 14 of 2010, s. 67(b).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_p:
  sectionId (72865)
  sectionNo 32P
  orderNo 90
  title `Proceedings before Settlement Commission to be judicial proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_p_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72865&sectionno=32P&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_p_content:
  string
  line `^1[32P. Proceedings before Settlement Commission to be judicial proceedings.--Any proceedings`
  line `under this Chapter before the Settlement Commission shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within`
  line `the meaning of Sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of Section 196 of the Indian Penal Code.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_pa:
  sectionId (72032)
  sectionNo 32PA
  orderNo 91
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_pa_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_pa_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72032&sectionno=32PA&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_32_pa_content:
  string
  line `^1[32PA. Certain persons who have filed appeals to the Appellate Tribunal entitled to make`
  line `applications to the Settlement Commission.-- Omitted by Finance Act 2007 (22 of 2007), s. 129 (w.e.f.`
  line `1-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_pa_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (72034)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 92
  title `Power of adjudication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72034&sectionno=33&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Power of adjudication.-- ^1[Where under this Act or by the rules made thereunder] anything is`
  line `liable to confiscation or any person is liable to a penalty, such confiscation or penalty may be adjudged--`
  line
  line `(a) without limit, by a ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central`
  line Excise];
  line
  line `(b) up to confiscation of goods not exceeding five hundred rupees in value and imposition of penalty`
  line `not exceeding two hundred and fifty rupees, by an Assistant ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central`
  line `Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise ^4[or Deputy ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise`
  line `or Commissioner of Central Excise]]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^3[Central Board of Excise and Customs constituted under the Central Boards of`
  line `Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963)], may, in the case of any officer performing the duties of an`
  line `Assistant ^2]Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise], reduce the`
  line `limits indicated in clause (b) of this section, and may confer on any officer the powers indicated in`
  line `clause (a) or (b) of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 125, for "Where by the rules made under this Act" (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 119.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 54 of 1963, s. 5, for "Central Board of Revenue" (w.e.f. 1-1-1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_a:
  sectionId (72035)
  sectionNo 33A
  orderNo 93
  title `Adjudication procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 81.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72035&sectionno=33A&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[33A. Adjudication procedure.--(1) The adjudicating authority shall, in any proceeding under this`
  line `chapter or any other provision of this Act, give an opportunity of being heard to a party in a proceeding, if`
  line `the party so desires.`
  line
  line `(2) The adjudicating authority may, if sufficient cause is shown, at any stage of proceeding referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1), grant time, from time to time, to the parties or any of them and adjourn the hearing for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such adjournment shall be granted more than three times to a party during the`
  line proceeding.]
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (72036)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 94
  title `Option to pay fine in lieu of confiscation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72036&sectionno=34&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Wherever confiscation is adjudged under this Act or`
  line `the rules made thereunder, the officer adjudging it, shall give the owner of the goods an option to pay in`
  line `lieu of confiscation such fine as the officer thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34_a:
  sectionId (72037)
  sectionNo 34A
  orderNo 95
  title `Confiscation or penalty not to interfere with other punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 22, (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72037&sectionno=34A&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[34A. Confiscation or penalty not to interfere with other punishments.--No confiscation made or`
  line `penalty imposed under the provisions of this Act or of any rule made thereunder shall prevent the infliction`
  line `of any other punishment to which the person affected thereby is liable under the provisions of this Act or`
  line `under any other law.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (72038)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 96
  title `Appeals to Commissioner (Appeals).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72038&sectionno=35&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `^1[35. Appeals to ^2[Commissioner (Appeals).--(1) Any person aggrieved by any decision or order`
  line `passed under this Act by a Central Excise Officer, lower in rank than a ^3[Principal Commissioner of Central`
  line `Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise], may appeal to the ^3[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise`
  line `or Commissioner of Central Excise] (Appeals) [hereafter in this Chapter referred to as the ^2[Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals)]]`
  line `^4[within sixty days] from the date of the communication to him of such decision or order:`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that the Commissioner (Appeals) may, if he is satisfied that the appellant was prevented`
  line `by sufficient cause from presenting the appeal within the aforesaid period of sixty days, allow it to be`
  line `presented within a further period of thirty days].`
  line
  line `^6[(1A) The Commissioner (Appeals) may, if sufficient cause is shown, at any stage of hearing of an`
  line `appeal, grant time, from time to time, to the parties or any of them and adjourn the hearing of the appeal`
  line `for reasons to be recorded in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such adjournment shall be granted more than three times to a party during hearing`
  line `of the appeal.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under this section shall be in the prescribed form and shall be verified in the prescribed`
  line manner.]]
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Substituted by Act 22 of 1995, s. 70, for "Collector (Appeals)" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 127, for "with three months" (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by ibid., s. 127, for proviso (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 82 (w.e.f. 10-9-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_a:
  sectionId (72039)
  sectionNo 35A
  orderNo 97
  title `Procedure in appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72039&sectionno=35A&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[35A. Procedure in appeal.--(1) The ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)] shall give an opportunity to the`
  line `appellant to be heard, if he so desires.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)] may, at the hearing of an appeal, allow an appellant to go into any`
  line `ground of appeal not specified in the grounds of appeal, if the ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)] is satisfied that`
  line `the omission of that ground from the grounds of appeal was not wilful or unreasonable.`
  line
  line `(3) ^3[The Commissioner (Appeals) shall, after making such further inquiry as may be necessary, pass`
  line `such order, as he thinks just and proper, confirming, modifying or annulling the decision or order appealed`
  line `against:]`
  line
  line `Provided that an order enhancing any penalty or fine in lieu of confiscation or confiscating goods`
  line `of greater value or reducing the amount of refund shall not be passed unless the appellant has been`
  line `given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the proposed order:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)] is of opinion that any duty of excise`
  line `has not been levied or paid or has been short-levied or short-paid or erroneously refunded, no order`
  line `requiring the appellant to pay any duty not levied or paid, short-levied or short-paid or erroneously`
  line `refunded shall be passed unless the appellant is given notice within the time-limit specified in Section`
  line `11A to show cause against the proposed order.`
  line
  line `(4) The order of the ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)] disposing of the appeal shall be in writing and shall`
  line `state the points for determination, the decision thereon and the reasons for the decision.`
  line
  line `^4[(4A) The Commissioner (Appeals) shall, where it is possible to do so, hear and decide every appeal`
  line `within a period of six months from the date on which it is filed.]`
  line
  line `(5) On the disposal of the appeal, the ^2[Commissioner (Appeals)] shall communicate the order passed`
  line `by him to the appellant, the adjudicating authority ^5[, the ^6[Principal Chief Commissioner of Central Excise`
  line `or Chief Commissioner of Central Excise]] and the ^7[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise].`
obj_root_law_sections_35_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Substituted by Act 22 of 1995, Section 70, for "Collector (Appeals)" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 128(a), for certain words (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by ibid., s. 128(b) (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 78.`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Chief Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by ibid., s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
obj_root_law_sections_35_b:
  sectionId (72040)
  sectionNo 35B
  orderNo 98
  title `Appeals to the Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72040&sectionno=35B&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[35B. Appeals to the Appellate Tribunal.--`
  line
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by any of the following orders`
  line `may appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against such order--`
  line
  line `(a) a decision or order passed by the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner`
  line `of Central Excise] as an adjudicating authority;`
  line
  line `(b) an order passed by the ^3[Commissioner (Appeals)] under Section 35-A;`
  line
  line `(c) an order passed by the Central Board of Excise and Customs constituted under the Central`
  line `Boards of Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963) (hereafter in this Chapter referred to as the Board) or the`
  line `Appellate ^3[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise under`
  line `Section 35, as it stood immediately before the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(d) an order passed by the Board or the ^4[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise], either before or after the appointed day, under Section 35-A, as it`
  line `stood immediately before that day:`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that no appeal shall lie to the Appellate Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal shall not`
  line `have jurisdiction to decide any appeal in respect of any order referred to in clause (b) if such order`
  line `relates to,--`
  line
  line `(a) a case of loss of goods, where the loss occurs in transit from a factory to a warehouse or to`
  line `another factory, or from one warehouse to another, or during the course of processing of the goods in`
  line `a warehouse or in storage, whether in a factory or in a warehouse;`
  line
  line `(b) a rebate of duty of excise on goods exported to any country or territory outside India or on`
  line `excisable materials used in the manufacture of goods which are exported to any country or territory`
  line `outside India;`
  line
  line `(c) goods exported outside India (except to Nepal or Bhutan) without payment of duty;`
  line
  line `^6[(d) credit of any duty allowed to be utilised towards payment of excise duty on final products`
  line `under the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder and such order is passed by the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals) on or after the date appointed under Section 109 of the Finance (No. 2) Act,`
  line `1998:]`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Appellate Tribunal may, in its discretion, refuse to admit an appeal in`
  line `respect of an order referred to in clause (b) or clause (c) or clause (d) where--`
  line
  line `(i) in any disputed case, other than a case where the determination of any question having a relation`
  line `to the rate of duty of excise or to the value of goods for purposes of assessment is in issue or is one of`
  line `the points in issue, the difference in duty involved or the duty involved; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the amount of fine or penalty determined by such order, does not exceed ^6[two lakh rupees].`
  line
  line `^7[(1A) Every appeal against any order of the nature referred to in the first proviso to sub-section (1),`
  line `which is pending immediately before the commencement of Section 47 of the Finance Act, 1984, before the Appellate Tribunal and any matter arising out of, or connected with, such appeal and which is so pending`
  line `shall stand transferred on such commencement to the Central Government, and the Central Government`
  line `shall deal with such appeal or matter under Section 35-EE as if such appeal or matter were an application`
  line `or a matter arising out of an application made to it under that section.]`
  line
  line `^8[(1B) (i) The Central Board of Excise and Customs constituted under the Central Boards of Revenue`
  line `Act, 1963 (54 of 1963) may, ^7[by order], constitute such Committees as may be necessary for the purposes`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `(ii) Every Committee constituted under clause (i) shall consist of two ^8[Principal Chief Commissioner`
  line `of Central Excise or Chief Commissioner of Central Excise] or two ^12[Principal Commissioner of Central`
  line `Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise], as the case may be.]`
  line
  line `^9[(2)`
  line `^10[The Committee of Commissioners of Central Excise may, if it is] is of opinion that an order`
  line `passed by the Appellate ^11[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise]`
  line `under Section 35, as it stood immediately before the appointed day, or the ^3[Commissioner (Appeals)] under`
  line `Section 35-A, is not legal or proper, direct any Central Excise Officer authorised by him in this behalf`
  line `(hereafter in this Chapter referred to as the authorised officer) to appeal ^13[on its behalf] to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal against such order.]`
  line
  line `^14[Provided that where the Committee of ^16[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner`
  line `of Central Excise] differs in its opinion regarding the appeal against the order of the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals), it shall state the point or points on which it differs and make a reference to the`
  line `jurisdictional ^17[Principal Chief Commissioner of Central Excise or Chief Commissioner of Central Excise]`
  line `who shall, after considering the facts of the order, if is of the opinion that the order passed by the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals) is not legal or proper, direct any Central Excise Officer to appeal to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal against such order.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "jurisdictional Chief Commissioner" means`
  line `the ^17[Principal Chief Commissioner of Central Excise or Chief Commissioner of Central Excise] having`
  line `jurisdiction over the adjudicating authority in the matter.]`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under this section shall be filed within three months from the date on which the order`
  line `sought to be appealed against is communicated to the ^18[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise], or, as the case may be, the other party preferring the appeal.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of notice that an appeal has been preferred under this section, the party against whom`
  line `the appeal has been preferred may, notwithstanding that he may not have appealed against such order or`
  line `any part thereof, file, within forty-five days of the receipt of the notice, a memorandum of cross-objections`
  line `verified in the prescribed manner against any part of the order appealed against and such memorandum`
  line `shall be disposed of by the Appellate Tribunal as if it were an appeal presented within the time specified in`
  line `sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The Appellate Tribunal may admit an appeal or permit the filing of a memorandum of crossobjections after the expiry of the relevant period referred to in sub-section (3) or sub-section (4), if it is`
  line `satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period.`
  line
  line `^19[(6) An appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be in the prescribed form and shall be verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner and shall, irrespective of the date of demand of duty and interest or of levy of penalty in`
  line `relation to which the appeal is made, be accompanied by a fee of,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the amount of duty and interest demanded and penalty levied by any Central Excise`
  line `Officer in the case to which the appeal relates is five lakh rupees or less, one thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(b) where the amount of duty and interest demanded and penalty levied by any Central Excise`
  line `Officer in the case to which the appeal relates is more than five lakh rupees but not exceeding fifty lakh`
  line `rupees, five thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(c) where the amount of duty and interest demanded and penalty levied by any Central Excise`
  line `Officer in the case to which the appeal relates is more than fifty lakh rupees, ten thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such fee shall be payable in the case of an appeal referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) or a memorandum of cross-objections referred to in sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(7) Every application made before the Appellate Tribunal,--`
  line
  line `(a) in an appeal ^20[* * *] for rectification of mistake or for any other purpose; or`
  line
  line `(b) for restoration of an appeal or an application,`
  line `shall be accompanied by a fee of five hundred rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such fee shall be payable in the case of an application filed by or on behalf of`
  line `the ^21[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] under this`
  line sub-section.]]
obj_root_law_sections_35_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by ibid., s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, Section 70, for "Collector (Appeals)" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 47, for "Provided that" (w.e.f. 11-5-1984).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 109 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 102(a), for "fifty thousand rupees".`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 47(b) (w.e.f. 11-5-1984).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 79.`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 102(b), for "by notification in the Official Gazette".`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by ibid, s. 95, for "Chief Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by ibid, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by Act 62 of 1986, s. 34(a)(i), for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 79, for "The Commissioner of Central Excise may, if he is".`
  line
  line `15. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 70, for "Collector (Appeals)" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `16. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 79(a)(ii), for "on his behalf".`
  line
  line `17. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 83.`
  line
  line `18. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `19. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 83, for sub-section (6) (w.e.f. 1-11-2004).`
  line
  line `20. The word "for grant of stay or" omitted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 102(c).`
  line
  line `21. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
obj_root_law_sections_35_c:
  sectionId (72041)
  sectionNo 35C
  orderNo 99
  title `Orders of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72041&sectionno=35C&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[35-C. Orders of Appellate Tribunal.--(1) The Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the parties to the`
  line `appeal an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, confirming, modifying or`
  line `annulling the decision or order appealed against or may refer the case back to the authority which passed`
  line `such decision or order with such directions as the Appellate Tribunal may think fit, for a fresh adjudication`
  line `or decision, as the case may be, after taking additional evidence, if necessary.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) The Appellate Tribunal may, if sufficient cause is shown, at any stage of hearing of an appeal,`
  line `grant time, from time to time, to the parties or any of them and adjourn the hearing of the appeal for reasons`
  line `to be recorded in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such adjournment shall be granted more than three times to a party during hearing`
  line `of the appeal.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Tribunal may, at any time within ^3[six months] from the date of the order, with a`
  line `view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record, amend any order passed by it under`
  line `sub-section (1) and shall make such amendments if the mistake is brought to its notice by the ^4[Principal`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] or the other party to the appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided that an amendment which has the effect of enhancing an assessment or reducing a refund`
  line `or otherwise increasing the liability of the other party, shall not be made under this sub-section, unless`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal has given notice to him of its intention to do so and has allowed him a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `^5[(2A) The Appellate Tribunal shall, where it is possible to do so, hear and decide every appeal within`
  line `a period of three years from the date on which such appeal is filed:`
  line
  line `^6[* * *]`
  line
  line `(3) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order passed under this section to the ^4[Principal`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] and the other party to the appeal.`
  line
  line `(4)`
  line `^7[Save as provided in the National Tax Tribunal Act, 2005] orders passed by the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `on appeal shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 84.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 140(i), for "four years".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line `5. Ins. by ibid, s. 140(ii).`
  line
  line `6. First, Second & Third Proviso omitted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 103.`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and Sch. (Pt. VII-5), for "Save as provided in section 35G or section 35L" (w.e.f. 28-12-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_d:
  sectionId (72042)
  sectionNo 35D
  orderNo 100
  title `Procedure of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72042&sectionno=35D&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[35D. Procedure of Appellate Tribunal.--(1) The provisions of sub-sections (1), (2), (5) and (6) of`
  line `Section 129-C of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962), shall apply to the Appellate Tribunal in the discharge`
  line `of its functions under this Act as they apply to it in the discharge of its functions under the Customs Act,`
  line `1962 (52 of 1962).`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line `^2[* * *]`
  line
  line `(3) The President or any other member of the Appellate Tribunal authorised in this behalf by the`
  line `President may, sitting singly, dispose of any case which has been allotted to the Bench of which he is a`
  line `member where--`
  line
  line `(a) in any disputed case, other than a case where the determination of any question having a relation`
  line `to the rate of duty of excise or to the value of goods for purposes of assessment is in issue or is one of`
  line `the points in issue, the difference in duty involved or the duty involved; or`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of fine or penalty involved, does not exceed ^3fifty lakh rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_35_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (2) omitted by Act 22 of 1995, s. 77 (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 99, for "ten lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 10-5-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_e:
  sectionId (72866)
  sectionNo 35E
  orderNo 101
  title `Powers of Committee of Principal Chief Commissioner of Central Excise or Chief Commissioners of Central Excise or Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioners of Central Excise to pass certain orders`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72866&sectionno=35E&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[35E. Powers of ^2[Committee of ^3[Principal Chief Commissioner of Central Excise or Chief`
  line `Commissioners of Central Excise] or ^4[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioners`
  line `of Central Excise]] to pass certain orders.--(1) The ^2[Committee of ^3[Principal Chief Commissioners of`
  line `Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise]] or may, of its own motion, call for and examine the`
  line `record of any proceeding in which a ^4[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of`
  line `Central Excis]] as an adjudicating authority has passed any decision or order under this Act for the purpose`
  line `of satisfying itself as to the legality or propriety of any such decision or order and may, by order, direct`
  line `such ^5[Commissioner ^6[or any other Commissioner]] to apply to the Appellate Tribunal ^7[or, as the case`
  line `may be, the Customs and Excise Revenues Appellate Tribunal established under Section 3 of the Customs`
  line `and Excise Revenues Appellate Tribunal Act, 1986] for the determination of such points arising out of the`
  line `decision or order as may be specified by the ^2[Committee of ^3[Principal Chief Commissioners of Central`
  line `Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise]] in its order:`
  line
  line `^8[Provided that where the Committee of ^9[Principal Chief Commissioners of Central Excise or Chief`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise[ differs in its opinion as to the legality or propriety of the decision or order`
  line `of the ^10[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise], it shall state the`
  line `point or points on which it differs and make a reference to the Board which, after considering the facts of`
  line `the decision or order, if is of the opinion that the decision or order passed by the ^10[Principal Commissioner`
  line `of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] is not legal or proper, may, by order, direct such`
  line `Commissioner or any other Commissioner to apply to the Appellate Tribunal for the determination of such`
  line `points arising out of the decision or order, as may be specified in its order.]`
  line
  line `(2) The ^10[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] may, of his`
  line `own motion, call for and examine the record of any proceeding in which an adjudicating authority`
  line `subordinate to him has passed any decision or order under this Act for the purpose of satisfying himself as`
  line `to the legality or propriety of any such decision or order and may, by order, direct ^11[such authority or any`
  line `Central Excise Officer subordinate to him to apply to the ^12[Commissioner (Appeals) for the determination`
  line `of such points arising out of the decision or order as may be specified by the ^10[Principal Commissioner of`
  line `Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] in his order.`
  line
  line `^13[(3) Every order under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), as the case may be, shall be made within a`
  line `period of three months from the date of communication of the decision or order of the adjudicating`
  line `authority:]`
  line
  line `^14[Provided that the Board may, on sufficient cause being shown, extend the said period by another thirty`
  line days.]
  line
  line `(4) Where in pursuance of an order under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the adjudicating authority`
  line `or the authorised officer makes an application to the Appellate Tribunal ^15[or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Customs and Excise Revenues Appellate Tribunal established under Section 3 of the Customs and Excise`
  line `Revenues Appellate Tribunal Act, 1986] or the ^12[Commissioner (Appeals) within a period of ^16[one month]`
  line `from the date of communication of the order under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) to the adjudicating`
  line `authority, such application shall be heard by the Appellate Tribunal ^15[or, as the case may be, the Customs`
  line `and Excise Revenues Appellate Tribunal established under Section 3 of the Customs and Excise Revenues`
  line `Appellate Tribunal Act, 1986 or the ^12[Commissioner (Appeals)], as the case may be, as if such application were an appeal made against the decision or order of the adjudicating authority and the provisions of this`
  line `Act regarding appeals, including the provisions of sub-section (4) of Section 35-B,`
  line `^17[or, as the case may be,`
  line `the provisions of the Customs and Excise Revenues Appellate Tribunal Act, 1986] shall, so far as may be,`
  line `apply to such application.`
  line
  line `^18[(5) The provisions of this section shall not apply to any decision or order in which the determination`
  line `of any question having a relation to the rate of duty of excise or to the value of goods for the purposes of`
  line `assessment of any duty is in issue or is one of the points in issue.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the determination of a rate of duty in relation`
  line `to any goods or valuation of any goods for the purposes of assessment of duty includes the`
  line `determination of a question--`
  line
  line `(a) relating to the rate of duty of excise for the time being in force, whether under the Central Excise`
  line `Tariff Act, 1985 (5 of 1986), or under any other Central Act providing for the levy and collection of`
  line `any duty of excise, in relation to any goods on or after the 28th day of February, 1986; or`
  line
  line `(b) relating to the value of goods for the purposes of assessment of any duty of excise in cases`
  line `where the assessment is made on or after the 28th day of February, 1986; or`
  line
  line `(c) whether any goods are excisable goods or whether the rate of duty of excise on any goods is nil;`
  line or
  line
  line `(d) whether any goods fall under a particular heading or sub-heading of the ^19[First Schedule and`
  line `the Second Schedule] to the Central Excise Tariff Act, 1985 (5 of 1986), or the Additional Duties of`
  line `Excise (Goods of Special Importance) Act, 1957 (58 of 1957), or the Additional Duties of Excise`
  line `(Textiles and Textile Articles) Act, 1978 (40 of 1978), or that any goods are or not covered by a`
  line `particular notification or order issued by the Central Government or the Board, as the case may be,`
  line `granting total or partial exemption from duty; or`
  line
  line `(e) whether the value of any goods for the purposes of assessment of duty of excise shall be`
  line `enhanced or reduced by the addition or reduction of the amounts in respect of such matters as are`
  line `specifically provided in this Act.]]`
  line
  line /hr
obj_root_law_sections_35_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 80, for "Board" (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Chief Commissioner of Central Excise" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by ibid., s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 70, for "Collector" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 129.`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 62 of 1986, s. 34, w.e.f. the appointed day under that Act.`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 84(i).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Chief Commissioner of Central Excise" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by ibid., s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise" (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 37, for "such authority".`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 70, for "Collector (Appeals)" (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 84(ii), for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 10-5-2008).`
  line
  line `14. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 104.`
  line
  line `15. Ins. by Act 62 of 1986, s. 34, w.e.f. the appointed day under that Act.`
  line
  line `16. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 130, for "three months".`
  line
  line `17. Ins. by Act 62 of 1986, s. 34, w.e.f. the appointed day under that Act.`
  line
  line `18. Ins. by Act 29 of 1988, s. 11 (w.e.f. a date to be notified).`
  line
  line `19. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 119, for "the Schedule".`
obj_root_law_sections_35_ea:
  sectionId (72867)
  sectionNo 35EA
  orderNo 102
  title `Powers of revision of Board or Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_ea_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_ea_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72867&sectionno=35EA&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_ea_content:
  string
  line `^1[35EA. Powers of revision of Board or ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise] in certain cases.--(1) The Board may, of its own motion or on the`
  line `application of any aggrieved person or otherwise, call for and examine the record of any proceeding in`
  line `which a ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] has passed any`
  line `decision or order not being a decision or order passed under sub-section (2) of this section] of the nature referred to in sub-section (5) of Section 35-E for the purpose of satisfying itself as to correctness, legality`
  line `or propriety of such decision or order and may pass such order thereon as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^3[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] may, of his`
  line `own motion or on the application of any aggrieved person or otherwise, call for and examine the record of`
  line `any proceeding in which an adjudicating authority subordinate to him has passed any decision or order of`
  line `the nature referred to in sub-section (5) of Section 35-E for the purpose of satisfying himself as to the`
  line `correctness, legality or propriety of such decision or order and may pass such order thereon as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) (a) No decision or order under this section shall be made so as to prejudicially affect any person`
  line `unless such person is given a reasonable opportunity of making representation and if, he so desires, of being`
  line `heard in his defence.`
  line
  line `(b) Where the Board or, as the case may be, the ^3[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise] is of the opinion that any duty of excise has not been levied or has been`
  line `short-levied or short-paid or erroneously refunded, no order requiring the affected person to pay any duty`
  line `not levied or paid, short-levied or short-paid or erroneously refunded shall be passed under this section`
  line `unless such person is given notice within the time-limit specified in Section 11-A to show cause against the`
  line `proposed order.`
  line
  line `(4) No proceedings shall be initiated under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) in respect of any decision`
  line `or order after the expiry of a period of six months from the date of communication of such decision or order:`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of any decision or order passed before the commencement of the Customs`
  line `and Central Excises Laws (Amendment) Act, 1988, the provisions of this sub-section shall have effect`
  line `as if for the words "six-months", the words "one year" were substituted.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person aggrieved by any decision or order passed under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) may`
  line `appeal to the Customs and Excise Revenues Appellate Tribunal established under Section 3 of the Customs`
  line `and Excise Revenues Appellate Tribunal Act, 1986 (62 of 1986), against such decision or order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_ea_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 1988, s. 12 (w.e.f. a date to be notified).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 62 of 1986, s. 34, w.e.f. the appointed day under that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_ee:
  sectionId (72045)
  sectionNo 35EE
  orderNo 103
  title `Revision by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_ee_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_ee_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72045&sectionno=35EE&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_ee_content:
  string
  line `@@^1[^2[35EE. Revision by Central Government.-- (1) The Central Government may, on the application of`
  line `any person aggrieved by any order passed under Section 35-A, where the order is of the nature referred to`
  line `in the first proviso to sub-section (1) of Section 35-B, annul or modify such order:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that the Central Government may in its discretion, refuse to admit an application in respect`
  line `of an order where the amount of duty or fine or penalty, determined by such order does not exceed five`
  line `thousand rupees.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "order passed under Section 35-A" includes an`
  line `order passed under that section before the commencement of Section 47 of the Finance Act, 1984 (21`
  line `of 1984) against which an appeal has not been preferred before such commencement and could have`
  line `been, if the said section had not come into force, preferred after such commencement, to the Appellate`
  line Tribunal.
  line
  line `^4(1A) The ^5Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise] may, if he`
  line `is of the opinion that an order passed by the Commissioner (Appeals) under Section 35-A is not legal or`
  line `proper, direct the proper officer to make an application on his behalf to the Central Government for revision`
  line `of such order.]`
  line
  line `(2) An application under sub-section (1) shall be made within three months from the date of the`
  line `communication to the applicant of the order against which the application is being made:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, if it is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by`
  line `sufficient cause from presenting the application within the aforesaid period of three months, allow it to`
  line `be presented within a further period of three months.`
  line
  line `^6(3) An application under sub-section (1) shall be in such form and shall be verified in such manner as`
  line `may be specified by rules made in this behalf and shall be accompanied by a fee of,--`
  line
  line `(a) two hundred rupees, where the amount of duty and interest demanded, fine or penalty levied by`
  line `any Central Excise Officer in the case to which the application relates is one lakh rupees or less;`
  line
  line `(b) one thousand rupees, where the amount of duty and interest demanded, fine or penalty levied`
  line `by any Central Excise Officer in the case to which the application relates is more than one lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such fee shall be payable in the case of an application referred to in sub-section`
  line `(1A).]`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, of its own motion, annul or modify any order referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(5) No order enhancing any penalty or fine in lieu of confiscation or confiscating goods of greater value--`
  line
  line `(a) in any case in which an order passed under Section 35A has enhanced any penalty or fine in`
  line `lieu of confiscation or has confiscated goods of greater value, and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, unless the person affected by the proposed order has been given notice to`
  line `show cause against it within one year from the date of the order sought to be annulled or modified.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the Central Government is of opinion that any duty of excise has not been levied or has been`
  line `short-levied, no order levying or enhancing the duty shall be made under this section unless the person`
  line `affected by the proposed order is given notice to show cause against it within the time-limit specified in`
  line `Section 11A.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_ee_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 50 (w.e.f. 11-5-1984).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 126(a) (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 126(b) (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 126(c), for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_f:
  sectionId (72046)
  sectionNo 35F
  orderNo 104
  title `Deposit of certain percentage of duty demanded or penalty imposed before filing appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_f_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_f_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72046&sectionno=35F&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[^2[35F. Deposit of certain percentage of duty demanded or penalty imposed before filing appeal.--`
  line `The Tribunal or the Commissioner (Appeals), as the case may be, shall not entertain any appeal--`
  line
  line `(i) under sub-section (1) of Section 35, unless the appellant has deposited seven and a half per cent`
  line `of the duty, in case where duty or duty and penalty are in dispute, or penalty, where such penalty is in`
  line `dispute, in pursuance of a decision or an order passed by an officer of Central Excise lower in rank than`
  line `the ^3[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise];`
  line
  line `(ii) against the decision or order referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of Section 35-B, unless`
  line `the appellant has deposited seven and a half per cent of the duty, in case where duty or duty and penalty`
  line `are in dispute, or penalty, where such penalty is in dispute, in pursuance of the decision or order`
  line `appealed against;`
  line
  line `(iii) against the decision or order referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of Section 35-B, unless`
  line `the appellant has deposited ten per cent of the duty, in case where duty or duty and penalty are in`
  line `dispute, or penalty, where such penalty is in dispute, in pursuance of the decision or order appealed`
  line `against:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount required to be deposited under this section shall not exceed Rupees`
  line `Ten crores:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the provisions of this section shall not apply to the stay applications and`
  line `appeals pending before any appellate authority prior to the commencement of the Finance (No. 2)`
  line `Act, 2014.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section "duty demandeddbqtd shall include,--`
  line
  line `(i) amount determined under Section 11D;`
  line
  line `(ii) amount of erroneous CENVAT credit taken;`
  line
  line `(iii) amount payable under Rule 6 of the CENVAT Credit Rules, 2001 or the CENVAT Credit`
  line `Rules, 2002 or the CENVAT Credit Rules, 2004.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_f_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 105, for section 35F (w.e.f. 6-8-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by ibid, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
obj_root_law_sections_35_ff:
  sectionId (72047)
  sectionNo 35FF
  orderNo 105
  title `Interest on delayed refund of amount deposited under Section 35-F.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_ff_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_ff_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72047&sectionno=35FF&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_ff_content:
  string
  line `^1[^2[35FF. Interest on delayed refund of amount deposited under Section 35F.--Where an amount`
  line `deposited by the appellant under Section 35F is required to be refunded consequent upon the order of the`
  line `appellate authority, there shall be paid to the appellant interest at such rate, not below five per cent and not`
  line
  line `exceeding thirty-six per cent per annum as is for the time being fixed by the Central Government, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, on such amount from the date of payment of the amount till, the date of`
  line `refund of such amount:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount deposited under Section 35F, prior to the commencement of the Finance`
  line `(No. 2) Act, 2014, shall continue to be governed by the provisions of Section 35FF as it stood before`
  line `the commencement of the said Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_ff_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by ibid, s. 106, for section 35FF.`
