obj_root_law_sections_35_k:
  sectionId (72052)
  sectionNo 35K
  orderNo 110
  title `Decision of High Court or Supreme Court on the case stated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_k_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_k_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72052&sectionno=35K&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_k_content:
  string
  line `^1[35K. Decision of High Court or Supreme Court on the case stated.--(1) The ^2[* * *] Supreme Court`
  line `hearing any such case shall decide the questions of law raised therein and shall deliver its judgment thereon`
  line `containing the grounds on which such decision is founded and a copy of the judgment shall be sent under`
  line `the seal of the Court and the signature of the Registrar to the Appellate Tribunal which shall pass such`
  line `orders as are necessary to dispose of the case in conformity with such judgment.`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) Where the High Court delivers a judgment in an appeal filed before it under Section 35G, effect`
  line `shall be given to the order passed on the appeal by the concerned Central Excise Officer on the basis of a`
  line `certified copy of the judgment.]`
  line
  line `(2) The costs of any ^4[reference to ^5[***] an appeal to ^5[* * *] the Supreme Court,^6[* * *]] which shall`
  line `not include the fee for making the reference shall be in the discretion of the Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_k_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. The words "High Court or the" omitted by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and Sch. (Pt. VII-7) (w.e.f. 28-12-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 146(a) (w.e.f. 1-7-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by ibid, s. 146, for "reference to the High Court or the Supreme Court" (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `5. The words "the High Court or"" omitted by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and Sch. (Pt. VII-7(ii)(a)) (w.e.f. 28-12-2005).`
  line
  line `6. The words "as the case may be" omitted by ibid, s. 30 and Sch. (Pt. VII-7(ii)(b)) (w.e.f. 28-12-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_l:
  sectionId (72053)
  sectionNo 35L
  orderNo 111
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_l_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_l_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72053&sectionno=35L&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_l_content:
  string
  line `^1[35L. Appeal to Supreme Court.-- ^2[(1) An appeal shall lie to the Supreme Court from--`
  line
  line `^3[(a) any judgment of the High Court delivered--`
  line
  line `(i) in an appeal made under Section 35G; or`
  line
  line `(ii) on a reference made under Section 35G by the Appellate Tribunal before the 1st day of July,`
  line 2003;
  line
  line `(iii) on reference made under Section 35H,`
  line `in any case which, on its own motion or on an oral application made by or on behalf of the party`
  line `aggrieved, immediately after the passing of the judgment, the High Court certifies to be a fit one for`
  line `appeal to the Supreme Court; or]`
  line
  line `(b) any order passed ^3[before the establishment of the National Tax Tribunal] by the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal relating, among other things, to the determination of any question having a relation to the rate`
  line `of duty of excise or to the value of goods for purposes of assessment.`
  line
  line `^4[(2) For the purposes of this Chapter, the determination of any question having a relation to the rate of`
  line `duty shall include the determination of taxability or excisability of goods for the purpose of assessment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_l_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Renumbered by Act 25 of 2014, s. 107.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 147, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and Sch. (Pt. VII-8) (w.e.f. 28-12-2005).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 107.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_m:
  sectionId (72054)
  sectionNo 35M
  orderNo 112
  title `Hearing before Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_m_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72054&sectionno=35M&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_m_content:
  string
  line `^1[35M. Hearing before Supreme Court.--(1) The provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908, (5`
  line `of 1908) relating to appeals to the Supreme Court shall, so far as may be, apply in the case of appeals under`
  line `Section 35L as they apply in the case of appeals from decrees of a High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed to affect the provisions of sub-section (1)`
  line `of Section 35K or Section 35N.`
  line
  line `(2) The costs of the appeal shall be in the discretion of the Supreme Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the judgment of the High Court is varied or reversed in the appeal, effect shall be given to`
  line `the order of the Supreme Court in the manner provided in Section 35-K in the case of a judgment of the`
  line `High Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_n:
  sectionId (72055)
  sectionNo 35N
  orderNo 113
  title `Sums due to be paid notwithstanding reference, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_n_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_n_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72055&sectionno=35N&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_n_content:
  string
  line `^1[35N. Sums due to be paid notwithstanding reference, etc.--Notwithstanding that a reference has`
  line `been made to the High Court or the Supreme Court or an appeal has been preferred to the Supreme`
  line `Court ^1[under this Act before the commencement of the National Tax Tribunal Act, 2005], sums due to the`
  line `Government as a result of an order passed under sub-section (1) of Section 35C shall be payable in`
  line `accordance with the order so passed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_n_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and Sch. (Pt. VII-9) (w.e.f. 28-12-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_o:
  sectionId (72056)
  sectionNo 35O
  orderNo 114
  title `Exclusion of time taken for copy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_o_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72056&sectionno=35O&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_o_content:
  string
  line `^1[35O. Exclusion of time taken for copy.--In computing the period of limitation prescribed for an`
  line `appeal or application under this Chapter, the day on which the order complained of was served, and if the`
  line `party preferring the appeal or making the application was not furnished with a copy of the order when the`
  line `notice of the order was served upon him, the time requisite for obtaining a copy of such order shall be`
  line excluded.]
obj_root_law_sections_35_p:
  sectionId (72057)
  sectionNo 35P
  orderNo 115
  title `Transfer of certain pending proceedings and transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_p_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_p_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72057&sectionno=35P&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_p_content:
  string
  line `^1[35P. Transfer of certain pending proceedings and transitional provisions.--(1) Every appeal which`
  line `is pending immediately before the appointed day before the Board under Section 35, as it stood immediately`
  line `before that day, and any matter arising out of or connected with such appeal and which is so pending shall`
  line `stand transferred on that day to the Appellate Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal may proceed with such`
  line `appeal or matter from the stage at which it was on that day:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellant may demand that before proceeding further with that appeal or matter,`
  line `he may be re-heard.`
  line
  line `(2) Every proceeding which is pending immediately before the appointed day before the Central`
  line `Government under Section 36, as it stood immediately before that day, and any matter arising out of or`
  line `connected with such proceeding and which is so pending shall stand transferred on that day to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal may proceed with such proceeding or matter from the stage at which`
  line `it was on that day as if such proceeding or matter were an appeal filed before it:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any such proceeding or matter relates to an order where--`
  line
  line `(a) in any disputed case, other than a case where the determination of any question having a relation`
  line `to the rate of duty of excise or to the value of goods for purposes of assessment is in issue or is one of`
  line `the points in issue, the difference in duty involved or the duty involved; or`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of fine or penalty determined by such order,`
  line
  line `does not exceed ten thousand rupees, such proceeding or matter shall continue to be dealt with by the`
  line `Central Government as if the said Section 36 had not been substituted:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the applicant or the other party may make a demand to the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `that before proceeding further with that proceeding or matter, he may be reheard.`
  line
  line `(3) Every proceeding which is pending immediately before the appointed day before the Board or`
  line `the ^2[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise under Section 35-A,`
  line `as it stood immediately before that day, and any matter arising out of or connected with such proceeding`
  line `and which is so pending shall continue to be dealt with by the Board or the ^2[Principal Commissioner of`
  line `Central Excise or Commissioner of Central Excise, as the case may be, as if the said section had not been`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `(4) Any person who immediately before the appointed day was authorised to appear in any appeal or`
  line `proceeding transferred under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall, notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in Section 35-Q, have the right to appear before the Appellate Tribunal in relation to such appeal or`
  line proceeding.]
obj_root_law_sections_35_p_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
obj_root_law_sections_35_q:
  sectionId (72058)
  sectionNo 35Q
  orderNo 116
  title `Appearance by authorised representative.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_q_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_q_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72058&sectionno=35Q&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_q_content:
  string
  line `^1[35Q. Appearance by authorised representative.--(1) Any person who is entitled or required to`
  line `appear before a Central Excise Officer or the Appellate Tribunal in connection with any proceedings under`
  line `this Act, otherwise than when required under this Act to appear personally for examination on oath or`
  line `affirmation, may, subject to the other provisions of this section, appear by an authorised representative.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, “authorised representative” means a person authorised by the person`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) to appear on his behalf, being--`
  line
  line `(a) his relative or regular employee; or`
  line
  line `(b) any legal practitioner who is entitled to practise in any civil court in India; or`
  line
  line `(c) any person who has acquired such qualifications as the Central Government may prescribe for`
  line `this purpose.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, no person who was a member of the Indian`
  line `Customs and Central Excise Service--Group A and has retired or resigned from such Service after having`
  line `served for not less than three years in any capacity in that Service, shall be entitled to appear as an authorised`
  line `representative in any proceedings before a Central Excise Officer for a period of two years from the date`
  line `of his retirement or resignation, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) No person,--`
  line
  line `(a) who has been dismissed or removed from Government service; or`
  line
  line `(b) who is convicted of an offence connected with any proceeding under this Act, the Customs Act,`
  line `1962 (52 of 1962) or the Gold (Control) Act, 1968 (45 of 1968)1 or`
  line
  line `(c) who has become an insolvent,`
  line
  line `shall be qualified to represent any person under sub-section (1), for all times in the case of a person`
  line `referred to in clause (a), and for such time as the ^3[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise or the competent authority under the Customs Act, 1962 or the Gold`
  line `(Control) Act, 1968 (45 of 1968)^2`
  line `, as the case may be, may, by order, determine in the case of a person`
  line `referred to in clause (b), and for the period during which the insolvency continues in the case of a person`
  line `referred to in clause (c).`
  line
  line `(5) If any person,--`
  line
  line `(a) who is a legal practitioner, is found guilty of misconduct in his professional capacity by any`
  line `authority entitled to institute proceedings against him, an order passed by that authority shall have effect in relation to his right to appear before a Central Excise Officer or the Appellate Tribunal as it has in`
  line `relation to his right to practise as a legal practitioner;`
  line
  line `(b) who is not a legal practitioner, is found guilty of misconduct in connection with any proceedings`
  line `under this Act by the prescribed authority, the prescribed authority may direct that he shall thenceforth`
  line `be disqualified to represent any person under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(6) Any order or direction under clause (d) of sub-section (4) or clause (b) of sub-section (5) shall be`
  line `subject to the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) no such order or direction shall be made in respect of any person unless he has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard;`
  line
  line `(b) any person against whom any such order or direction is made may, within one month of the`
  line `making of the order or direction, appeal to the Board to have the order or direction cancelled; and`
  line
  line `(c) no such order or direction shall take effect until the expiration of one month from the making`
  line `thereof, or, where an appeal has been preferred, until the disposal of the appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_q_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Repealed by Act 18 of 1990, s. 2.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
obj_root_law_sections_35_r:
  sectionId (72059)
  sectionNo 35R
  orderNo 117
  title `Appeal not to be filed in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_r_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_r_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72059&sectionno=35R&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_35_r_content:
  string
  line `^1[^2[35R. Appeal not to be filed in certain cases.--(1) The Central Board of Excise and Customs may,`
  line `from time to time, issue orders or instructions or directions fixing such monetary limits, as it may deem fit,`
  line `for the purposes of regulating the filing of appeal, application, revision or reference by the Central Excise`
  line `Officer under the provisions of this chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, in pursuance of the orders or instructions or directions, issued under sub-section (1), the`
  line `Central Excise Officer has not filed an appeal, application, revision or reference against any decision or`
  line `order passed under the provisions of this Act, it shall not preclude such Central Excise Officer from filing`
  line `appeal, application, revision or reference in any other case involving the same or similar issues or questions`
  line `of law.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding the fact that no appeal, application, revision or reference has been filed by the`
  line `Central Excise Officer pursuant to the orders or instructions or directions issued under sub-section (1), no`
  line `person, being a party in appeal, application, revision or reference shall contend that the Central Excise`
  line `Officer has acquiesced in the decision on the disputed issue by not filing appeal, application, revision or`
  line reference.
  line
  line `(4)`
  line `^3[The Commissioner (Appeals) or the Appellate Tribunal or court hearing such appeal, application,`
  line `revision or reference shall have regard to the circumstances under which appeal, application, revision or`
  line `reference was not filed by the Central Excise Officer in pursuance of the orders or instructions or directions`
  line `issued under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(5) Every order or instruction or direction issued by the Central Board of Excise and Customs on or`
  line `after the 20th day of October, 2010, but before the date on which the Finance Bill, 2011 receives the assent`
  line `of the President, fixing monetary limits for filing of appeal, application, revision or reference shall be`
  line `deemed to have been issued under sub-section (1) and the provisions of sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) shall`
  line `apply accordingly.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_r_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 50 and Schedule V, Pt. II-2, for sections 35, 35A and 36 (w.e.f. 11-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 69 (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 108, for "The Appellate Tribunal or court".`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (72060)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 118
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72060&sectionno=36&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day " means the date^1 of coming into force of the amendments to this Act specified`
  line `in Part II of the Fifth Schedule to the Finance (No. 2) Act, 1980 (44 of 1980);`
  line
  line `(b) "High Court " means,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to any State, the High Court for that State;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a Union Territory to which the jurisdiction of the High Court of a State has`
  line `been extended by law, that High Court;`
  line
  line `(iii) in relation to the Union Territories of Dadra and Nagar Haveli and ^2]Daman and Diu,] the`
  line `High Court at Bombay;`
  line
  line `(iv) in relation to any other Union Territory, the highest court of civil appeal for that territory`
  line `other than the Supreme Court of India;`
  line
  line `(c) "President " means the President of the Appellate Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Came into force on 11-10-1982 vide G.S.R. 592 (E), dated 11th October, 1982.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 1989 the Goa, Daman & Diu Reorganisation Act, 1987 (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_36_a:
  sectionId (72061)
  sectionNo 36A
  orderNo 119
  title `Presumption as to documents in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1973, s. 23.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72061&sectionno=36A&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_36_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[36A. Presumption as to documents in certain cases.--Where any document is produced by any`
  line `person or has been seized from the custody or control of any person, in either case, under this Act or under`
  line `any other law and such document is tendered by the prosecution in evidence against him or against him and`
  line `any other person who is tried jointly with him, the Court shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) unless the contrary is proved by such person, presume--`
  line
  line `(i) the truth of the contents of such document;`
  line
  line `(ii) that the signature and every other part of such document which purports to be in the`
  line `handwriting of any particular person or which the Court may reasonably assume to have been`
  line `signed by, or to be in the handwriting of, any particular person, is in that person's handwriting, and in the case of a document executed or attested, that it was executed or attested by the person by`
  line `whom it purports to have been so executed or attested;`
  line
  line `(b) admit the document in evidence, notwithstanding that it is not duly stamped, if such document`
  line `is otherwise admissible in evidence.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_b:
  sectionId (72868)
  sectionNo 36B
  orderNo 120
  title `Admissibility of microfilms, facsimile copies of documents and computer printouts as documents and as evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 1988, S. 13 (w.e.f. 1-7-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72868&sectionno=36B&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_36_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[36B. Admissibility of microfilms, facsimile copies of documents and computer printouts as`
  line `documents and as evidence.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being`
  line `in force,--`
  line
  line `(a) a microfilm of a document or the reproduction of the image or images embodied in such`
  line `microfilm (whether enlarged or not); or`
  line
  line `(b) a facsimile copy of a document; or`
  line
  line `(c) a statement contained in a document and included in a printed material produced by a computer`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as a "computer printout"), if the conditions mentioned in sub-section (2) and`
  line `the other provisions contained in this section are satisfied in relation to the statement and the computer`
  line `in question,`
  line `shall be deemed to be also a document for the purposes of this Act and the rules made thereunder`
  line `and shall be admissible in any proceedings thereunder, without further proof or production of the`
  line `original, as evidence of any contents of the original or of any fact stated therein of which direct evidence`
  line `would be admissible.`
  line
  line `(2) The conditions referred to in sub-section (1) in respect of a computer printout shall be the following,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the computer printout containing the statement was produced by the computer during the period`
  line `over which the computer was used regularly to store or process information for the purposes of any`
  line `activities regularly carried on over that period by the person having lawful control over the use of the`
  line computer;
  line
  line `(b) during the said period, there was regularly supplied to the computer in the ordinary course of`
  line `the said activities, information of the kind contained in the statement or of the kind from which the`
  line `information so contained is derived;`
  line
  line `(c) throughout the material part of the said period, the computer was operating properly or, if not,`
  line `then any respect in which it was not operating properly or was out of operation during that part of that`
  line `period was not such as to affect the production of the document or the accuracy of the contents; and`
  line
  line `(d) the information contained in the statement reproduced or is derived from information supplied`
  line `to the computer in the ordinary course of the said activities.`
  line
  line `(3) Where over any period, the function of storing or processing information for the purposes of any`
  line `activities regularly carried on over that period as mentioned in clause (a) of sub-section (2) was regularly`
  line `performed by computers, whether--`
  line
  line `(a) by a combination of computers operating over that period; or`
  line
  line `(b) by different computers operating in succession over that period; or`
  line
  line `(c) by different combinations of computers operating in succession over that period; or`
  line
  line `(d) in any other manner involving the successive operation over that period, in whatever order, of`
  line `one or more computers and one or more combinations of computers,`
  line
  line `all the computers used for that purpose during that period shall be treated for the purposes of this`
  line `section as constituting a single computer; and references in this section to a computer shall be construed`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(4) In any proceedings under this Act and the rules made thereunder where it is desired to give a`
  line `statement in evidence by virtue of this section, a certificate doing any of the following things, that is to`
  line say,--
  line
  line `(a) identifying the document containing the statement and describing the manner in which it was`
  line produced;
  line
  line `(b) giving such particulars of any device involved in the production of that document as may be`
  line `appropriate for the purpose of showing that the document was produced by a computer;`
  line
  line `(c) dealing with any of the matters to which the conditions mentioned in sub-section (2) relate,`
  line
  line `and purporting to be signed by a person occupying a responsible official position in relation to the`
  line `operation of the relevant device or the management of the relevant activities (whichever is appropriate)`
  line `shall be evidence of any matter stated in the certificate; and for the purposes of this sub-section it shall`
  line `be sufficient for a matter to be stated to the best of the knowledge and belief of the person stating it.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) information shall be taken to be supplied to a computer if it is supplied thereto in any appropriate`
  line `form and whether it is so supplied directly or (with or without human intervention) by means of any`
  line `appropriate equipment;`
  line
  line `(b) whether in the course of activities carried on by any official, information is supplied with a view`
  line `to its being stored or processed for the purposes of those activities by a computer operated otherwise`
  line `than in the course of those activities, that information, if duly supplied to that computer, shall be taken`
  line `to be supplied to it in the course of those activities;`
  line
  line `(c) a document shall be taken to have been produced by a computer whether it was produced by it`
  line `directly or (with or without human intervention) by means of any appropriate equipment.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "computer" means any device that receives, stores and processes data, applying stipulated`
  line `processes to the information and supplying results of these processes; and`
  line
  line `(b) any reference to information being derived from other information shall be a reference to its`
  line `being derived therefrom by calculation, comparison or any other process.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (72064)
