obj_root_law_sections_37_b:
  sectionId (72066)
  sectionNo 37B
  orderNo 123
  title `Instructions to Central Excise Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72066&sectionno=37B&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_37_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[37B. Instructions to Central Excise Officers.--The Central Board of Excise and Customs`
  line `constituted under the Central Boards of Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963), may, if it considers it necessary`
  line `or expedient so to do for the purpose of uniformity in the classification of excisable goods or with respect`
  line `to levy of duties of excise on ^2[such goods or for the implementation of any other provision of this Act],`
  line `issue such orders, instructions and directions to the Central Excise Officers as it may deem fit, and such`
  line `officers and all other persons employed in the execution of this Act shall observe and follow such orders,`
  line `instructions and directions of the said Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such orders, instructions or directions shall be issued--`
  line
  line `(a) so as to require any Central Excise Officer to make a particular assessment or to dispose of a`
  line `particular case in a particular manner; or`
  line
  line `(b) so as to interfere with the discretion of the ^3[Principal Commissioner of Central Excise or`
  line `Commissioner of Central Excise (Appeals) in the exercise of his appellate functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sections 37B & 37C ins. by Act 79 of 1985, s. 7 (w.e.f. 27-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 144, for "such goods" (w.e.f. 14-5-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
obj_root_law_sections_37_c:
  sectionId (72067)
  sectionNo 37C
  orderNo 124
  title `Service of decisions, orders, summons, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72067&sectionno=37C&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_37_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[37C. Service of decisions, orders, summons, etc.--(1) Any decision or order passed or any`
  line `summons or notices issued under this Act or the rules made thereunder, shall be served,--`
  line
  line `(a) by tendering the decision, order, summons or notice, or sending it by registered post with`
  line `acknowledgment due ^2[or by speed post with proof of delivery or by courier approved by the Central`
  line `Board of Excise and Customs constituted under the Central Boards of Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963)],`
  line `to the person for whom it is intended or his authorised agent, if any;`
  line
  line `(b) if the decision, order, summons or notice cannot be served in the manner provided in clause (a),`
  line `by affixing a copy thereof to some conspicuous part of the factory or warehouse or other place of`
  line `business or usual place of residence of the person for whom such decision, order, summons or notice,`
  line `as the case may be, is intended;`
  line
  line `(c) if the decision, order, summons or notice cannot be served in the manner provided in clauses`
  line `(a) and (b), by affixing a copy thereof on the notice-board of the officer or authority who or which`
  line `passed such decision or order or issued such summons or notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Every decision or order passed or any summons or notice issued under this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder, shall be deemed to have been served on the date on which the decision, order, summons or`
  line `notice is tendered or delivered by post ^3[or courier referred to in sub-section (1)] or a copy thereof is affixed`
  line `in the manner provided in sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_37_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 95, for "Commissioner of Central Excise".`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 100(i).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 100(ii)`
obj_root_law_sections_37_d:
  sectionId (72068)
  sectionNo 37D
  orderNo 125
  title `Rounding off of duty, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 65 (w.e.f. 31-5-1990).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72068&sectionno=37D&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_37_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[37D. Rounding off of duty, etc.--The amount of duty, interest, penalty, fine or any other sum`
  line `payable, and the amount of refund or any other sum due, under the provisions of this Act shall be rounded`
  line `off to the nearest rupee and, for this purpose, where such amount contains a part of a rupee consisting of`
  line `paise then, if such part is fifty paise or more, it shall be increased to one rupee and if such part is less than`
  line `fifty paise it shall be ignored.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37_e:
  sectionId (72069)
  sectionNo 37E
  orderNo 126
  title `Publication of information respecting persons in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act. 29 of 2006, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-9-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72069&sectionno=37E&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_37_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[37E. Publication of information respecting persons in certain cases.--(1) If the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient in the public interest to publish the names of any`
  line `person and any other particulars relating to any proceedings or prosecutions under this Act in respect of`
  line `such person, it may cause to be published such names and particulars in such manner as if thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) No publication under this section shall be made in relation to any penalty imposed under this Act`
  line `until the time for presenting an appeal to the Commissioner (Appeals) under Section 35 of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal under Section 35-B, as the case may be, has expired without an appeal having been presented or`
  line `the appeal, if presented, has been disposed of.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In the case of a firm, company or other association of persons, the names of the`
  line `partners of the firm, directors, managing agents, secretaries and treasurers or managers of the company,`
  line `or the members of the association, as the case may be, may also be published if, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, circumstances of the case justify it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (72070)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 127
  title `Publication of rules and notifications and laying of rules before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72070&sectionno=38&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `^1[38. Publication of rules and notifications and laying of rules before Parliament.--(1) All rules`
  line `made and notifications issued under this Act shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
  line `^2[(2) Every rule made under this Act, every notification issued under ^3[Section 3A, ^4[Section 3C]`
  line `Section 4A,] sub-section (1) of Section 5A, ^5[Section 5B] and Section 11C and every order made under`
  line `sub-section (2) of Section 5A, other than an order relating to goods of strategic, secret, individual or`
  line `personal nature, shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made or issued, before each House of Parliament,`
  line `while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session, or in two or`
  line `more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or notification or`
  line `order, or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made or notification or order should not be issued`
  line `or made, the rule or notification or order shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice`
  line `to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or notification or order.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1973, s. 4, for section 38.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 79, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 26-5-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 84 (w.e.f. 14-5-1997).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 2017, s. 9.`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 70.`
