  title `Effect of amendments, etc. of rules, notifications or orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 131 (w.r.e.f. 28-2-1944).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438&sectionId=72071&sectionno=38A&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_A1944-01_1671705649438
obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[38A. Effect of amendments, etc. of rules, notifications or orders.--Where any rule, notification or`
  line `order made or issued under this Act or any notification or order issued under such rule, is amended,`
  line `repealed, superseded or rescinded, then, unless a different intention appears, such amendment, repeal,`
  line `supersession or rescinding shall not--`
  line
  line `(a) revive anything not in force or existing at the time at which the amendment, repeal, supersession`
  line `or rescinding takes effect; or`
  line
  line `(b) affect the previous operation of any rule, notification or order so amended, repealed, superseded`
  line `or rescinded or anything duly done or suffered thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(c) affect any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under any rule,`
  line `notification or order so amended, repealed, superseded or rescinded; or`
  line
  line `(d) affect any penalty, forfeiture or punishment incurred in respect of any offence committed under`
  line `or in violation of any rule, notification or order so amended, repealed, superseded or rescinded; or`
  line
  line `(e) affect any investigation, legal proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege,`
  line `obligation, liability, penalty, forfeiture or punishment as aforesaid,`
  line `and any such investigation, legal proceeding or remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced`
  line `and any such penalty, forfeiture or punishment may be imposed as if the rule, notification or order, as`
  line `the case may be, had not been amended, repealed, superseded or rescinded.]`
